thub.com/siralam/BSImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6925\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/siralam/BSImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6935\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6889\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6850\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6807\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6779\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6778\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6782\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://github.com/mreram/TicketView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6799\" target=\"_blank\">http://github.com/mreram/TicketView</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Refrence: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://android-arsenal.com/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Libs And Tools','','inherit','closed','closed','','201-revision-v1','','','2019-01-05 13:28:47','2019-01-05 13:28:47','',201,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/05/201-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(266,1,'2019-01-05 13:44:51','2019-01-05 13:44:51','<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"width\":255,\"height\":255} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft is-resized\"><img src=\"http://appsfeature.com/images/aj_logo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"255\" height=\"255\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nHe loves learning new stuff in Android and iOS. Shoot him queries.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Admin Login : </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://blogs.appsfeature.com/wp-admin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">http://blogs.appsfeature.com/wp-admin</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','About Abhijit Rao','','inherit','closed','closed','','8-revision-v1','','','2019-01-05 13:44:51','2019-01-05 13:44:51','',8,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/05/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2019-01-09 07:00:14','2019-01-09 07:00:14','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gradle is a build automation tool often used for JVM languages such as Java, Groovy or Scala. Gradle can be configured to run&nbsp;<code>Tasks</code>&nbsp;which do things like compile&nbsp;<code>jar</code>s, run tests, create documentation and much more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gardle is an advanced general purpose build management. It is an open source build automation system that builds up on ANT, Maven and lvy repositories. It supports groovy based Domain Specific Language (DSL) over the XML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"build-process\">The build process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process involves many tools and processes that convert your project into an Android Application Package (APK). The build process is very flexible, so it\'s useful to understand some of what is happening under the hood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":475,\"height\":534} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://developer.android.com/images/tools/studio/build-process_2x.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"534\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Figure 1.</strong>&nbsp;The build process of a typical Android app module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process for a typical Android app module, as shown in figure 1, follows these general steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The compilers convert your source code into DEX (Dalvik Executable) files, which include the bytecode that runs on Android devices, and everything else into compiled resources.</li><li>The APK Packager combines the DEX files and compiled resources into a single APK. Before your app can be installed and deployed onto an Android device, however, the APK must be signed.</li><li>The APK Packager signs your APK using either the debug or release keystore:<ol type=\"a\"><li>If you are building a debug version of your app, that is, an app you intend only for testing and profiling, the packager signs your app with the debug keystore. Android Studio automatically configures new projects with a debug keystore.</li><li>If you are building a release version of your app that you intend to release externally, the packager signs your app with the release keystore. To create a release keystore, read about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/publish/app-signing.html#studio\">signing your app in Android Studio</a>.</li></ol></li><li>Before generating your final APK, the packager uses the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/command-line/zipalign.html\">zipalign</a>&nbsp;tool to optimize your app to use less memory when running on a device.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the build process, you have either a debug APK or release APK of your app that you can use to deploy, test, or release to external users.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Gradle configuration</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>General structure.</strong>&nbsp;Follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/index.html\">Google\'s guide on Gradle for Android</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>minSdkVersion: 21</strong>&nbsp;We recommend to have a look at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/index.html#Platform\">Android version usage chart</a>&nbsp;before defining the minimum API required. Remember that the statistics given are global statistics and may differ when targeting a specific regional/demographic market. It is worth mentioning that some material design features are only available on Android 5.0 (API level 21) and above. And also, from API 21, the multidex support library is not needed anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <br><strong>Passwords.</strong>&nbsp;In your app\'s&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;you will need to define the&nbsp;<code>signingConfigs</code>&nbsp;for the release build. Here is what you should avoid: <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Don\'t do this</strong></em><strong>. </strong>This would appear in the version control system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\">signingConfigs </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\">release </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// DON\'T DO THIS!!</span>\n        storeFile file(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n        storePassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password123\"</span>\n        keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n        keyPassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password789\"</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead, make a&nbsp;<code>gradle.properties</code>&nbsp;file which should&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;be added to the version control system:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=password123\nKEY_PASSWORD=password789\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That file is automatically imported by Gradle, so you can use it in&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;as such:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">signingConfigs {\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            storeFile <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">file</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n            storePassword KEYSTORE_PASSWORD\n            keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n            keyPassword KEY_PASSWORD\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">ex</span>) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throw</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> InvalidUserDataException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"You should define KEYSTORE_PASSWORD and KEY_PASSWORD in gradle.properties.\"</span>)\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Use different package name for non-release builds</strong>&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use&nbsp;<code>applicationIdSuffix</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<em>debug</em><a href=\"http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/new-build-system/user-guide#TOC-Build-Types\">build type</a>&nbsp;to be able to install both&nbsp;<em>debug</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>release</em>&nbsp;apk on the same device (do this also for custom build types, if you need any). This will be especially valuable after your app has been published. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    buildTypes {\n        debug {\n            applicationIdSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'.debug\'</span>\n            versionNameSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'-DEBUG\'</span>\n        }\n\n        release {\n            // ...\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"building_gradle_minify\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#building_gradle_minify\">Removing unused resources and Java classes via resource shrinking</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Gradle build system for Android supports resource shrinking at build time. This automatically removes resources that are unused from the packaged application. In addition to that, this also removes unnecessary resources from libraries you are depending on. This can hugely reduce the size of your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To enable resource shrinking, update your build file similar to the following snippet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    ...\n\n    buildTypes {\n        release {\n            minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            shrinkResources <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-android.txt\'), <span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-rules.pro\'\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\">Defining dependencies and keeping the version external</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"bb4a\">1. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Module level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">25</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n    playServiceVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    \n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n   ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_12\">2. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Project level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>build.gradle(Project level)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">buildscript {\n    ...\n}\n\nallprojects {\n    ...\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'23.4.0\'</span>\n    playServicesVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'9.2.1\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> build.gradle(Module level) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span> \n\n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>  \n    ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Proguard</strong> <strong>configuration</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://proguard.sourceforge.net/\">ProGuard</a>&nbsp;is normally used on Android projects to shrink and obfuscate the packaged code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you are using ProGuard or not depends on your project configuration. Usually you would configure Gradle to use ProGuard when building a release APK.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">buildTypes</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">debug</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">minifyEnabled</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>\n    }\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">signingConfig</span> signingConfigs.release\n        minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n        proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-android.txt\'</span>), <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-rules.pro\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to determine which code has to be preserved and which code can be discarded or obfuscated, you have to specify one or more entry points to your code. These entry points are typically classes with main methods, applets, midlets, activities, etc. Android framework uses a default configuration which can be found from&nbsp;<code>SDK_HOME/tools/proguard/proguard-android.txt</code>. Using the above configuration, custom project-specific ProGuard rules, as defined in&nbsp;<code>my-project/app/proguard-rules.pro</code>, will be appended to the default configuration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A common problem related to ProGuard is to see the application crashing on startup with&nbsp;<code>ClassNotFoundException</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code>NoSuchFieldException</code>&nbsp;or similar, even though the build command (i.e.&nbsp;<code>assembleRelease</code>) succeeded without warnings. This means one out of two things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>ProGuard has removed the class, enum, method, field or annotation, considering it\'s not required.</li><li>ProGuard has obfuscated (renamed) the class, enum or field name, but it\'s being used indirectly by its original name, i.e. through Java reflection.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/usage.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been removed. Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been obfuscated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>stripping away</em>&nbsp;needed classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keep</code>&nbsp;options to your ProGuard config:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keep class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>obfuscating</em>&nbsp;classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keepnames</code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keepnames class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read more at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.guardsquare.com/en/proguard/manual/examples\">Proguard</a>&nbsp;for examples.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Early in your project, make and test release build</strong>&nbsp;to check whether ProGuard rules are correctly retaining your dependencies. Also whenever you include new libraries or update their dependencies, make a release build and test the APK on a device. Don\'t wait until your app is finally version \"1.0\" to make a release build, you might get several unpleasant surprises and a short time to fix them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip.</strong>&nbsp;Save the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for every release that you publish to your users. By retaining a copy of the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for each release build, you ensure that you can debug a problem if a user encounters a bug and submits an obfuscated stack trace.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>DexGuard</strong>. If you need hard-core tools for optimizing, and specially obfuscating release code, consider&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.saikoa.com/dexguard\">DexGuard</a>, a commercial software made by the same team that built ProGuard. It can also easily split Dex files to solve the 65k methods limitation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"leakcanary\">LeakCanary</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary is a memory leak detection library for Android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":649,\"height\":315} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img src=\"https://github.com/square/leakcanary/wiki/assets/screenshot-2.0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"649\" height=\"315\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary’s knowledge of the internals of the Android Framework gives it a unique ability to narrow down the cause of each leak, helping developers dramatically reduce OutOfMemoryError crashes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Add LeakCanary to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n  // <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation because LeakCanary should only run <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">in</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span> builds.\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation \'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android:<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2.0</span>-alpha-<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">3</span>\'\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>That’s it, there is no code change needed!</strong>&nbsp;LeakCanary will automatically show a notification when a memory leak is detected in debug builds.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/\">https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How do I exclude all instances of a transitive dependency when using Gradle?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can exclude a transitive dependency either by configuration or by dependency: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span>.all {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.webkit\"</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"webkit\"</span>\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fileTree</span>(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'*.jar\'</span>], dir: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'libs\'</span>) \n    implementation(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.1.0\"</span>) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.fragment\'</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'fragment\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Or</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'axiom-compat\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'javax.servlet\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'commons-fileupload\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.apache.woden\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'javax.ws.rs\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// axiom-api</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'jaxen\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.apache.geronimo.specs\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'apache-mime4j-core\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// neethi</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.codehaus.woodstox\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to implement Remote binary dependency</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implementation</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android:app-magic:12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is actually shorthand for the following:<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">implementation <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">name</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'app-magic\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">version</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This declares a dependency on version 12.3 of the \"app-magic\" library, inside the \"com.example.android\" namespace group.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','publish','open','open','','android-gradle','','','2019-10-22 08:48:57','2019-10-22 07:48:57','',0,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/?p=269',0,'post','',0),(270,1,'2019-01-09 06:59:58','2019-01-09 06:59:58','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49711773/how-to-recompile-with-xlintdeprecation\">How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to <code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','inherit','closed','closed','','269-revision-v1','','','2019-01-09 06:59:58','2019-01-09 06:59:58','',269,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/09/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(272,1,'2019-01-09 07:30:09','2019-01-09 07:30:09','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49711773/how-to-recompile-with-xlintdeprecation\">How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"building_gradle_minify\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#building_gradle_minify\">Removing unused resources and Java classes via resource shrinking</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Gradle build system for Android supports resource shrinking at build time. This automatically removes resources that are unused from the packaged application. In addition to that, this also removes unnecessary resources from libraries you are depending on. This can hugely reduce the size of your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To enable resource shrinking, update your build file similar to the following snippet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    ...\n\n    buildTypes {\n        release {\n            minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            shrinkResources <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-android.txt\'), <span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-rules.pro\'\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\">Defining dependencies and keeping the version external</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"bb4a\">1. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Module level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">25</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n    playServiceVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    \n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n   ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_12\">2. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Project level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>build.gradle(Project level)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">buildscript {\n    ...\n}\n\nallprojects {\n    ...\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'23.4.0\'</span>\n    playServicesVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'9.2.1\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> build.gradle(Module level) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span> \n\n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>  \n    ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','inherit','closed','closed','','269-revision-v1','','','2019-01-09 07:30:09','2019-01-09 07:30:09','',269,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/09/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(274,1,'2019-01-11 08:43:27','2019-01-11 08:43:27','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely popular and are often used in almost any Android project. Each has different purposes but all of them make life as a developer much more pleasant. The major libraries are listed below in a few categories.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_10\">OCRSdk</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Text Detector from image for react native using Google Vision API on android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ocrsdk:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage Method</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">     scanner = OCRSdk.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).addListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> OCRListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onSuccess(StringBuilder result) {\n                tvStatus.setText(result);\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedLines(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; lines) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedWords(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; words) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onFailure(Exception e) {\n\n            }\n        });\n        scanner.addTextView(tvStatus, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> SentenceDetector.OnClickListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onClick(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> word) {\n\n            }\n        });\n\n        scanner.startScanning();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"markdown-header-progressbutton\">ProgressButton</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nShow button with progress bar\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Android Button that morphs into a loading progress bar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Fully customizable in the XML</li><li>Really simple to use.</li><li>Makes your app looks cooler</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/73ab06601fb650fd51fa01781053fde8ff52f9bd/68747470733a2f2f692e737461636b2e696d6775722e636f6d2f38534852312e676966\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Setup\nAdd this <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">to</span> your project build.gradle\n\nallprojects {\n    repositories {\n        maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Dependency\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//before androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButton:1.0\'</span>\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//after androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButtonX:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Usage\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// In your activity_main.xml class:</span>\n\n &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span> layout=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@layout/button_progress\"</span>/&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for activity</span>\nView rootView = activity.getWindow().getDecorView().getRootView();\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for fragment pass layout reference in view</span>\nrootView = view;\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//  Initialization method</span>\nbtnAction = ProgressButton.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, rootView)\n        .setText(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Send Request\"</span>)\n        .setOnClickListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> View.OnClickListener() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onClick</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(View v)</span> </span>{\n            }\n        });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Update progress bar methods</span>\n     \n      btnAction.startProgress();\n\n    \n      btnAction.revertSuccessProgress(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ProgressButton.Listener() {\n          @Override\n          public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onAnimationCompleted() {\n          }\n      });\n      \n      btnAction.revertProgress();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CoreLib</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This library contains Android Button which can morph to Circular Progress,    Progress manager used for showing progress bar during making http request with success and failure response handler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link:  <br><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib\" target=\"_blank\">https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>DBInterface</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> SQLite databases is tough while developing. You cannot view the tables, you don\'t know what is getting inserted into the tables and you can\'t update the data and see how your application responds to it. What if you had a database manager like oracle sql developr, mysql work bench for your application\'s SQLite database? This library gives you that. With this library you can manage the database of your android app from the app itself. You can view, insert, delete, update the tables of your app\'s SQLite database from your app. <strong><br>Also Support Android Room Library</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Github link:  <a href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_1\">FirebaseConfig</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setup firebase Remote Config and Crashlist for validating user and crash reporting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link :<br><a href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\">ht</a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\">tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig</a><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"markdown-header-exporter\">Exporter</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Export support in following format: (txt, csv, xls) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Text file</li><li>CSV file</li><li>Excel file</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-dependency\">Dependency</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<embed type=\"image/svg+xml\" src=\"https://jitpack.io/v/org.bitbucket.droidhelios/Exporter.svg\">\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:Exporter:x.y\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-prepare-list-for-this-library\">Prepare List for this library</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; getExporterList() {\n        List&lt;User&gt; yourList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"01\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Alpha\"</span>));\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"02\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Bita\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//add header in your exporting list</span>\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Id\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Name\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//make exporter list</span>\n        List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; exporterList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> (User item : yourList){\n            exporterList.add(Arrays.asList(item.getId(),item.getName()));\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> exporterList;\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-text-file\">Export in Text file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).TextBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleText\"</span>)\n            .setFileBody(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello World!\"</span>)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-csv-file\">Export in CSV file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).CsvBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleCsv\"</span>)\n            .setCsvData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-excel-file\">Export in Excel file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).ExcelBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleExcel\"</span>)\n            .setExcelData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Success\"</span>, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>\n\nFor showing list of files.\n\n</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> exportCsv.showListOfFiles(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Selector&lt;File&gt;() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSelect</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n            shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n        }\n    });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Must Have Libraries For Android Developer','','publish','open','open','','must-have-libraries-for-android-developer','','','2019-11-09 07:06:52','2019-11-09 07:06:52','',0,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/?p=274',0,'post','',0),(275,1,'2019-01-11 08:42:17','2019-01-11 08:42:17','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThere are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely popular and are often used in almost any Android project. Each has different purposes but all of them make life as a developer much more pleasant. The major libraries are listed below in a few categories.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>DBInterface</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> SQLite databases is tough while developing. You cannot view the tables, you don\'t know what is getting inserted into the tables and you can\'t update the data and see how your application responds to it. What if you had a database manager like oracle sql developr, mysql work bench for your application\'s SQLite database? This library gives you that. With this library you can manage the database of your android app from the app itself. You can view, insert, delete, update the tables of your app\'s SQLite database from your app. <strong><br>Also Support Android Room Library</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Github:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\">https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->','Must Have Libraries For Android Developer','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2019-01-11 08:42:17','2019-01-11 08:42:17','',274,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/11/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(276,1,'2019-01-14 12:39:15','2019-01-14 12:39:15','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"a5b2\">Converting callback async calls to&nbsp;RxJava</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>APIs usually offer one of these two options when dealing with expensive operations:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>A&nbsp;<strong>synchronous</strong>&nbsp;blocking method call (expected to be called from a background thread)</li><li>An&nbsp;<strong>asynchronous</strong>&nbsp;non-blocking method call that uses callbacks (and/or listeners, broadcast receivers, etc)</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"a5e7\">Converting synchronous APIs to Observables</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the first type of APIs, RxJava offers a convenient factory method named <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/rx/Observable.html#fromCallable%28java.util.concurrent.Callable%29\" target=\"_blank\">Observable.fromCallable()</a>. For example, this is how it would look to convert the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/SharedPreferences.Editor.html\" target=\"_blank\">commit method from Android’s SharedPreferences API</a>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// wrapping synchronous operation in an RxJava Observable</span>\nObservable&lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span>&gt; wipeContents(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> SharedPreferences sharedPreferences) { \n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> Observable.fromCallable(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callable&lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span>&gt;() { \n        @Override \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">call</span>() <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throws</span> Exception { \n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> sharedPreferences.edit().clear().commit(); \n        } \n    }); \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/yammer-engineering/converting-callback-async-calls-to-rxjava-ebc68bde5831\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://medium.com/yammer-engineering/converting-callback-async-calls-to-rxjava-ebc68bde5831</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','RxJava2','','publish','open','open','','rxjava2','','','2019-01-14 12:39:18','2019-01-14 12:39:18','',0,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/?p=276',0,'post','',0),(277,1,'2019-01-14 12:39:15','2019-01-14 12:39:15','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"a5b2\">Converting callback async calls to&nbsp;RxJava</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>APIs usually offer one of these two options when dealing with expensive operations:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>A&nbsp;<strong>synchronous</strong>&nbsp;blocking method call (expected to be called from a background thread)</li><li>An&nbsp;<strong>asynchronous</strong>&nbsp;non-blocking method call that uses callbacks (and/or listeners, broadcast receivers, etc)</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"a5e7\">Converting synchronous APIs to Observables</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the first type of APIs, RxJava offers a convenient factory method named <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/rx/Observable.html#fromCallable%28java.util.concurrent.Callable%29\" target=\"_blank\">Observable.fromCallable()</a>. For example, this is how it would look to convert the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/SharedPreferences.Editor.html\" target=\"_blank\">commit method from Android’s SharedPreferences API</a>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// wrapping synchronous operation in an RxJava Observable</span>\nObservable&lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span>&gt; wipeContents(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> SharedPreferences sharedPreferences) { \n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> Observable.fromCallable(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callable&lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span>&gt;() { \n        @Override \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Boolean</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">call</span>() <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throws</span> Exception { \n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> sharedPreferences.edit().clear().commit(); \n        } \n    }); \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/yammer-engineering/converting-callback-async-calls-to-rxjava-ebc68bde5831\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://medium.com/yammer-engineering/converting-callback-async-calls-to-rxjava-ebc68bde5831</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','RxJava2','','inherit','closed','closed','','276-revision-v1','','','2019-01-14 12:39:15','2019-01-14 12:39:15','',276,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/14/276-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(278,1,'2019-01-16 08:25:26','2019-01-16 08:25:26','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Browse sample code to learn how to build different components for your applications.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This section covers useful codes for Java Android Programming. Every example program includes the description of the program, Java Android code, explanation as well as output of the program. <br>Below are Android Code Examples, Tutorials and projects to make android applications:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">HomeListData</span></span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span>&lt;ClassModel&gt; getClassModels(){\n        ...\n        ...\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;() ;\n        }\n    }\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> void initClassModel(){\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            Method method = HomeListData.class.getMethod(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"getClassModels\"</span>);\n            Object o = method.invoke(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span> );\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( o <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span> Collection<span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">&lt;?</span>&gt;){\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span> = (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span>) o ;\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span>.size() &gt; <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span> &amp;&amp; <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span>.get(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span>  ClassModel ) {\n                    classModels = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> ( Object classModel :  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span> ) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( classModel <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span> ClassModel ) {\n                            classModels.add((ClassModel)classModel);\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (NoSuchMethodException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (IllegalAccessException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (InvocationTargetException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        }<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">finally</span> {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( classModels == <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span> || classModels.size() &lt; <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span> ){\n                finish();\n            }\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Android TextView : “Do not concatenate text displayed with setText”</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> helloWorld = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"World\"</span>);\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> count = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world_count, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>);\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> totalCount = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Total : $count\"</span>;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> world <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">position</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'$s\'</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;Hello - %s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> hello world\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;%<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s - %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">numeric</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">value</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world_count\"</span>&gt;%d Item Selected&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    // example\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"welcome_messages\"</span>&gt;Hello, %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s! You have %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$d <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> messages.&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">using</span> getString(R.string.welcome_message, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Test\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t get confused with&nbsp;<strong>%1$s</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>%2$d</strong>&nbsp;in the accepted answer.Here is a few extra information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The format specifiers can be of the following syntax:</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>%[<code>argument_index</code>$]<code>format_specifier</code></p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The optional&nbsp;<strong>argument_index</strong>&nbsp;is specified as a number ending with a “$” after the “%” and selects the specified argument in the argument list. The first argument is referenced by&nbsp;<strong>\"1$\"</strong>, the second by&nbsp;<strong>\"2$\"</strong>, etc.</li><li>The required&nbsp;<strong>format specifier</strong>&nbsp;is a character indicating how the argument should be formatted. The set of valid conversions for a given argument depends on the argument\'s&nbsp;<strong>data type.</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_3\">How can I show the shadow only on the bottom side of the layout </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nAn important thing here is the attribute&nbsp;<code>outlineProvider</code>, that is required to make the outer Layout cast a shadow even without having a background set.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"xml\"><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span> \n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_width</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"match_parent\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_height</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"wrap_content\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:background</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@android:color/white\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:elevation</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"2dp\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:outlineProvider</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"bounds\"</span> &gt;</span>\n <span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span>&gt;</span>\n</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Validate URL</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">boolean</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">isValidURL</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String urlStr)</span> </span>{\n          <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>  Patterns.WEB_URL.matcher(urlStr).matches();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>UI post delay by time interval using Handler</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler().postDelayed(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{ \n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// write your code here</span>\n            }\n        }, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">400</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Useful for small background tasks</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//        Declear in class </span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> Handler <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span> = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Thread(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Try to sleep the thread for 20 milliseconds</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    Thread.sleep(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">20</span>);  <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//3 seconds</span>\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (InterruptedException e) {\n                    e.printStackTrace();\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Update the progress bar</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span>.post(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//                             updateUi()</span>\n                    }\n                });\n            }\n        }).start(); <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Start the operation</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>How do I escape a single quote in SQL Query</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">word</span>.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">replace</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\'\"</span>)</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Http request using webView  </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> void callWebviewAuth() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web = (WebView)findViewById();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.getSettings().setJavaScriptEnabled(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearCache(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearHistory(); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.loadUrl(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"https://www.facebook.com/v2.6/dialog/oauth?redirect_uri=fb464891386855067%3A%2F%2Fauthorize%2F&amp;scope=user_birthday,user_photos,user_education_history,email,user_relationship_details,user_friends,user_work_history,user_likes&amp;response_type=token%2Csigned_request&amp;client_id=464891386855067\"</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient(){\n            String authCode;\n            boolean authComplete = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>;\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onFormResubmission(WebView webView, Message message, Message message2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onFormResubmission(webView, message, message2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onLoadResource(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onLoadResource(webView, string2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*\n             * Enabled aggressive block sorting\n             */</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageFinished(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageFinished(webView, string2); \n                Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1 = string2;\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"access_token=\"</span>) &amp;&amp; !<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.authComplete) {\n                     \n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (!string2.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"error=access_denied\"</span>)) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    {\n                        \n                        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageStarted(WebView webView, String string2, Bitmap bitmap) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageStarted(webView, string2, bitmap);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4388992/key-hash-for-android-facebook-app\">Key hash for Android-&nbsp;Facebook&nbsp;Login</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the steps-</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Download openssl from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8k_WIN32.zip\"><strong>Google code</strong></a>&nbsp;(If you have a 64 bit machine you must&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8e_X64.zip&amp;can=2&amp;q=\"><strong>download openssl-0.9.8e X64</strong></a>&nbsp;not the latest version)</li><li>Extract it. create a folder- OpenSSL in C:/ and copy the extracted code here.</li><li>detect debug.keystore file path. If u didn\'t find, then do a search in C:/ and use the Path in the command in next step.</li><li>open cmd and change directory cd \"C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_191\\bin\" </li><li>run keytool command mentioned below.<ul><li>it will ask for password, put android</li><li>that\'s all. u will get a key-hash </li></ul></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">keytool -exportcert -alias androiddebugkey -keystore \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">Users</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">kkk</span></span>.android<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">debug</span></span>.keystore\" | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" sha1 -binary | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" base64</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Pass data in fragment using Arguments</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThe underlying Binder transaction buffer has a limited fixed size, currently 1Mb, which is shared by all transactions in progress for the process.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> static Fragment newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data1, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data2, ArrayList&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>) {\n        Fragment fragment = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Fragment(); \n        Bundle bundle = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Bundle();\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data1\"</span>, data1);\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data2\"</span>, data2);\n        bundle.putParcelableArrayList(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"list\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>);\n        fragment.setArguments(bundle); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> fragment;\n    }\n    \n    @Override\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onCreate(@Nullable Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span>(getArguments()!=<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" s