1\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/shagiz/AsyncFilePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/siralam/BSImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6925\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/siralam/BSImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6935\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6889\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6850\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6807\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6779\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6778\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6782\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://github.com/mreram/TicketView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6799\" target=\"_blank\">http://github.com/mreram/TicketView</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Refrence: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://android-arsenal.com/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Libs And Tools','','inherit','closed','closed','','201-revision-v1','','','2019-01-30 10:28:42','2019-01-30 10:28:42','',201,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/30/201-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(316,1,'2019-01-31 09:45:07','2019-01-31 09:45:07','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Java Generics</strong>&nbsp;programming is introduced in J2SE 5 to deal with type-safe objects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Before generics, we can store any type of objects in collection i.e. non-generic. Now generics, forces the java programmer to store specific type of objects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Advantage of Java Generics</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are mainly 3 advantages of generics. They are as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1)	Type-safety :</strong>&nbsp;We can hold only a single type of objects in generics. It doesn’t allow to store other objects.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2)	Type casting is not required:</strong>&nbsp;There is no need to typecast the object.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Generic class</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> A class that can refer to any type is known as generic class. Here, we are using&nbsp;<strong>T</strong>&nbsp;type parameter to create the generic class of specific type. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    MyGen&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; myGen = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> MyGen&lt;&gt;();\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Add data</span>\n    myGen.add(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data\"</span>);\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//get data</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> output = myGen.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">get</span>();\n     \n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyGen</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">T</span>&gt; </span>{\n        T obj;\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> add(T obj) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.obj = obj;\n        }\n\n        T <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">get</span>() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> obj;\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Type Parameters</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The type parameters naming conventions are important to learn generics thoroughly. The commonly type parameters are as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>T - Type</li><li>E - Element</li><li>K - Key</li><li>N - Number</li><li>V - Value</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Generic Method</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like generic class, we can create generic method that can accept any type of argument.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s see a simple example of java generic method to print array elements. We are using here&nbsp;<strong>E</strong>&nbsp;to denote the element.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">TestGenerics4</span>{  \n  \n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> &lt; E &gt; <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">printArray</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">E[] elements</span>) </span>{  \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> ( E element : elements){          \n            System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println(element );  \n         }  \n         System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println();  \n    }  \n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">main</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> String args[] </span>) </span>{  \n        Integer[] intArray = { <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">20</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">30</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">40</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">50</span> };  \n        Character[] charArray = { <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'J\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'A\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'V\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'A\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'T\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'P\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'O\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'I\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'N\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'T\'</span> };  \n  \n        System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println( <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Printing Integer Array\"</span> );  \n        printArray( intArray  );   \n  \n       System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println( <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Printing Character Array\"</span> );  \n        printArray( charArray );   \n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wildcard in Java Generics</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The ? (question mark) symbol represents wildcard element. It means any type. If we write &lt;? extends Number&gt;, it means any child class of Number e.g. Integer, Float, double etc. Now we can call the method of Number class through any child class object.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s understand it by the example given below:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> void draw();\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Rectangle</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        void draw() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">System</span>.out.println(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"drawing rectangle\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Circle</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        void draw() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">System</span>.out.println(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"drawing circle\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">GenericTest</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//creating a method that accepts only child class of Shape  </span>\n        public static void drawShapes(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;? <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Shape</span>&gt; lists) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> (<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Shape</span> s : lists) {\n                s.draw();<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//calling method of Shape class by child class instance  </span>\n            }\n        }\n\n        public static void main(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> args[]) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>&gt; list1 = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">ArrayList</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>&gt;();\n            list1.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>());\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>&gt; list2 = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">ArrayList</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>&gt;();\n            list2.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>());\n            list2.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>());\n\n            drawShapes(list1);\n            drawShapes(list2);\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example 1</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> interface Callback&lt;T&gt; {\n        <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;T&gt; response);\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onError(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> error);\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> GenericTypeExample() {\n        backgroundJob(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Callback&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt;() {\n            @Override\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; response) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Log</span>.e(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"onSuccess\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"List size\"</span> + response.size());\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onError(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> error) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Log</span>.e(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"onError\"</span>, error);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> backgroundJob(Callback&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; callback) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> = getList();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> != <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) {\n            callback.onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>);\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n            callback.onError(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Empty List\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> &lt;T&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;T&gt; getList() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n    }\n\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example 2</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Service</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">T</span>&gt; </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\">T <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">execute</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">FooService</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implements</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Service</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">String</span>&gt; </span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> String input1;\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> input2;\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">FooService</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String input1, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> input2)</span> </span>{\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.input1 = input1;\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.input2 = input2;\n        }\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">execute</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> String.format(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'%s%d\'\"</span>, input1, input2);\n        }\n    }\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example 3</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">main</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>{\n        TextView tvProfile = getViewFromId(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"tv_profile\"</span>, TextView.class, getActivityRootView());\n        ImageView ivProfile = getViewFromId(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"iv_profile\"</span>, ImageView.class, getActivityRootView());\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> &lt;T&gt; <span class=\"hljs-function\">T <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">getViewFromId</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String resourceName, Class&lt;T&gt; type, View rootView)</span> </span>{\n        T t = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span>;\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> resourceId = getDynamicId(resourceName);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (resourceId != <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span> &amp;&amp; rootView != <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span>) {\n            t = type.cast(rootView.findViewById(resourceId));\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> t;\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">getDynamicId</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String id)</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> getResources().getIdentifier(id, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"id\"</span>, getPackageName());\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (Exception e) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>;\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> View <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">getActivityRootView</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> getWindow().getDecorView().getRootView();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Generics in Java','','publish','open','open','','generics-in-java','','','2019-07-06 07:04:47','2019-07-06 06:04:47','',0,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/?p=316',0,'post','',0),(317,1,'2019-01-31 09:45:07','2019-01-31 09:45:07','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Generic class</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> A class that can refer to any type is known as generic class. Here, we are using <strong>T</strong> type parameter to create the generic class of specific type. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyGen</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">T</span>&gt; </span>{\n        T obj;\n\n        void add(T obj) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.obj = obj;\n        }\n\n        T <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">get</span>() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> obj;\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Type Parameters</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The type parameters naming conventions are important to learn generics thoroughly. The commonly type parameters are as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>T - Type</li><li>E - Element</li><li>K - Key</li><li>N - Number</li><li>V - Value</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Generic Method</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like generic class, we can create generic method that can accept any type of argument.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let’s see a simple example of java generic method to print array elements. We are using here <strong>E</strong> to denote the element.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">TestGenerics4</span>{  \n  \n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> &lt; E &gt; <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">printArray</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">E[] elements</span>) </span>{  \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> ( E element : elements){          \n            System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println(element );  \n         }  \n         System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println();  \n    }  \n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">main</span>(<span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> String args[] </span>) </span>{  \n        Integer[] intArray = { <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">20</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">30</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">40</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">50</span> };  \n        Character[] charArray = { <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'J\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'A\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'V\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'A\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'T\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'P\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'O\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'I\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'N\'</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'T\'</span> };  \n  \n        System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println( <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Printing Integer Array\"</span> );  \n        printArray( intArray  );   \n  \n       System.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">out</span>.println( <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Printing Character Array\"</span> );  \n        printArray( charArray );   \n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wildcard in Java Generics</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The ? (question mark) symbol represents wildcard element. It means any type. If we write &lt;? extends Number&gt;, it means any child class of Number e.g. Integer, Float, double etc. Now we can call the method of Number class through any child class object.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s understand it by the example given below:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> void draw();\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Rectangle</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        void draw() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">System</span>.out.println(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"drawing rectangle\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Circle</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Shape</span> </span>{\n        void draw() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">System</span>.out.println(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"drawing circle\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">GenericTest</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//creating a method that accepts only child class of Shape  </span>\n        public static void drawShapes(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;? <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Shape</span>&gt; lists) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> (<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Shape</span> s : lists) {\n                s.draw();<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//calling method of Shape class by child class instance  </span>\n            }\n        }\n\n        public static void main(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> args[]) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>&gt; list1 = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">ArrayList</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>&gt;();\n            list1.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Rectangle</span>());\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>&gt; list2 = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">ArrayList</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>&gt;();\n            list2.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>());\n            list2.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Circle</span>());\n\n            drawShapes(list1);\n            drawShapes(list2);\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example 1</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> interface Callback&lt;T&gt; {\n        <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;T&gt; response);\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onError(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> error);\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> GenericTypeExample() {\n        backgroundJob(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Callback&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt;() {\n            @Override\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; response) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Log</span>.e(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"onSuccess\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"List size\"</span> + response.size());\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onError(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> error) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">Log</span>.e(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"onError\"</span>, error);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> backgroundJob(Callback&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; callback) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> = getList();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> != <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) {\n            callback.onSuccess(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>);\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n            callback.onError(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Empty List\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> &lt;T&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;T&gt; getList() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n    }\n\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Example 2</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Service</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">T</span>&gt; </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\">T <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">execute</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">FooService</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implements</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Service</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">String</span>&gt; </span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> String input1;\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> input2;\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">FooService</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String input1, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> input2)</span> </span>{\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.input1 = input1;\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.input2 = input2;\n        }\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">execute</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> String.format(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'%s%d\'\"</span>, input1, input2);\n        }\n    }\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Generics in Java','','inherit','closed','closed','','316-revision-v1','','','2019-01-31 09:45:07','2019-01-31 09:45:07','',316,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/01/31/316-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2019-02-06 13:00:06','2019-02-06 13:00:06','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Showcase View</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ECLaboratorio/BubbleShowCase-Android.git\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/ECLaboratorio/BubbleShowCase-Android.git</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/mreram/ShowCaseView.git\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mreram/ShowCaseView.git</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7357\">EasyFlipViewPager</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div align=\"center\"><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/book_flip_demo.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7357\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/poker_demo.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7357\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/gallery_demo.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7357\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><h2></h2><br><img width=\"280px\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/gallery_demo.gif\"></a><img width=\"280px\" hspace=\"20\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/poker_demo.gif\"><img width=\"280px\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyFlipViewPager/master/Art/book_flip_demo.gif\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7359\">Hauler</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Hauler is a library containing custom layout which enables to easily create swipe to dismiss&nbsp;<code>Activity</code>. Implementation is based on code from project&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/nickbutcher/plaid?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7359\" target=\"_blank\">Plaid</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/thefuntasty/hauler\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/thefuntasty/hauler</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thefuntasty/hauler/master/images/example.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7362\">Easy CSV</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Creates csv file for android </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/hsmnzaydn/easy-csv\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/hsmnzaydn/easy-csv</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7364\">Text Scanner from image</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This library extend&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developers.google.com/vision/?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7364\" target=\"_blank\">google vision</a>&nbsp;. And initilay it read text from image. for reading text from image you have to give image&nbsp;<strong>Uri</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>Bitmap</strong>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/mahimrocky/TextRecognizer\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mahimrocky/TextRecognizer</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mahimrocky/TextRecognizer/master/screenshot.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7366\">Choreographer</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Animate views easily by chaining animations, run them serially or in parallel. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/ZachBublil/Choreographer\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/ZachBublil/Choreographer</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ZachBublil/Choreographer/master/demoGif.gif\" alt=\"\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7367\">BottomSheetTimeRangePicker</a></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>BottomSheetPickers is a tiny Android library for adding Date and Time Pickers as Modal BottomSheetDialogs with From and To ranges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The library is inspired by Titto Jose\'s&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/tittojose/TimeRangePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7367\" target=\"_blank\">TimeRangePicker</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/adawoud/BottomSheetTimeRangePicker\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/adawoud/BottomSheetTimeRangePicker</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adawoud/BottomSheetTimeRangePicker/master/art/bottomsheetpicker.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7376\">android-imagecropview</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> An Android library that lets you implement image crop. ImageCropView crops image by moving image under fixed crop area like instagram and iOS. Image zoom in/out is base on&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/sephiroth74/ImageViewZoom?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7376\" target=\"_blank\">sephiroth74\'s imageViewZoom. Sample app is base on&nbsp;</a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developers.aviary.com/?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7376\" target=\"_blank\">aviary SDK sample.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/naver/android-imagecropview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/naver/android-imagecropview</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/naver/android-imagecropview/master/doc/img/pholar.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7417\">Payment Card View</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/manojbhadane/PaymentCardView\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/manojbhadane/PaymentCardView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/manojbhadane/PaymentCardView/master/PaymentCardView.png\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption><br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7407\">Dynamic Toasts</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/hotstu/ZebraTextView\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/hotstu/ZebraTextView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> A simple library to display themed toasts with icon and text on Android 9+ (Gingerbread or above) devices. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pranavpandey/dynamic-toasts/master/graphics/dynamic-toasts-preview.png\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption><br></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7401\">Material Toast</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/marcoscgdev/MaterialToast\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/marcoscgdev/MaterialToast</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA fully and highly customizable material designed Toast for Android.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/marcoscgdev/MaterialToast/master/device-2018-12-22-164932.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7351\">StateViews</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/kobeumut/StateViews\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/kobeumut/StateViews</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Create &amp; Show progress, data or error views, the easy way! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kobeumut/StateViews/master/art/StatusPage.jpg\" alt=\"\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7334\">Country code dialog picker</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/BartNijland91/android-countrycodepickerdialog\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/BartNijland91/android-countrycodepickerdialog</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BartNijland91/android-countrycodepickerdialog/master/screenshot.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7340\">Cyanea</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/jaredrummler/Cyanea\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/jaredrummler/Cyanea</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA powerful, dynamic, and fun theme engine. Named after Octopus Cyanea which is adept at camouflage and not only can change color frequently, but also can change the patterns on and texture of its skin.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\">\n<a>\n<img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/7f7f7520d61f2f704ff12d6d31b7cafe601263e4/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f6543366435574f2e676966\" alt=\"\">\n</a>\n<a>\n<img align=\"left\" hspace=\"10\" src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/b0cdc1242d8170b8184ef2a92d8afd5af4152563/68747470733a2f2f692e696d6775722e636f6d2f706a44456a576c2e676966\">\n</a>\n</figure> \n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/3/7342\">CurvedBottomNavigationView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/androidtutorialonline/CurvedBottomNavigationView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/androidtutorialonline/CurvedBottomNavigationView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nwe will learn How to draw custom shapes in Curved Bottom Navigation View\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/7cf1dee61362f29a0abd06248d8b439a5323130f/68747470733a2f2f7777772e616e64726f69647475746f7269616c6f6e6c696e652e636f6d2f77702d636f6e74656e742f75706c6f6164732f323031382f31312f426f74746f6d4e617669676174696f6e566965772e676966\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7350\">FloatingToast</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/hariprasanths/FloatingToast\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/hariprasanths/FloatingToast</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nAn android library to make customisable floating animated toasts\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/b469bd7e9f684420b89eab81e7c91fecd6c9831d/68747470733a2f2f6d656469612e67697068792e636f6d2f6d656469612f5a784c624c76557434394f3057744c4575662f67697068792e676966\" alt=\"\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7306\">Hidden SearchView in RecyclerView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/lnicolet/HiddenSearchWithRecyclerView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/lnicolet/HiddenSearchWithRecyclerView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> An easy way to search in your recycler view without having an always-on display search view. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lnicolet/HiddenSearchWithRecyclerView/master/default_example.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7316\">SMS view</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/SmsView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/SmsView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VRGsoftUA/SmsView/master/preview.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7320\">CameraViewEx</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/pvasa/cameraview-ex\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/pvasa/cameraview-ex</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nCameraViewEx makes integration of camera implementation and various camera features into any Android project very easy.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nCameraViewEx requires minimum API level 14. The library uses Camera1 API on API Level 14-20 and Camera2 on API level 21 and above.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7292\">Android Scratchcard</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/myinnos/AndroidScratchCard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/myinnos/AndroidScratchCard</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nLight Weighted Scratchcard View Library for Android\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/myinnos/AndroidScratchCard/master/images-gif/androidscratchcard-example.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7278\">AndroidVeil</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/skydoves/AndroidVeil\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/skydoves/AndroidVeil</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A library that lets you implement skeletons and shimmer animation for veiling layouts and recyclerView.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\">\n\n<p><a href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24237865/47777293-c736d780-dd37-11e8-9107-5242746a7b8c.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7278\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24237865/47777293-c736d780-dd37-11e8-9107-5242746a7b8c.gif\" hspace=\"20\"></a> <a href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24237865/47781860-1aae2300-dd42-11e8-8c5c-a2417b03b74d.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7278\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24237865/47781860-1aae2300-dd42-11e8-8c5c-a2417b03b74d.gif\"></a></p>\n\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7281\">ParallaxView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nView container which applies parallax effect to its content. You can Even achieve 3d effect if you use two containers, one atop another like on video below.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\">\n<a href=\"https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView/blob/master/scroll1.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7281\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"https://github.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView/blob/master/scroll2.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7281\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"270\" height=\"480\" hspace=\"20\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView/master/scroll2.gif\"></a><img width=\"270\" height=\"480\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VRGsoftUA/ParallaxView/master/scroll1.gif\"><br><br> \n\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7282\">WP7ProgressBar</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/shadowalker77/wp7progressbar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/shadowalker77/wp7progressbar</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThis library aims to bring awesome windows phone 7 and windows 10 progress bar to android applications. Here is the example:\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/shadowalker77/wp7progressbar/master/ScreenShots/wp10.gif\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"20\">\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/shadowalker77/wp7progressbar/master/ScreenShots/wp7.gif\">\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7287\">SimpleSearchView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Ferfalk/SimpleSearchView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/Ferfalk/SimpleSearchView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A simple SearchView for Android based on Material Design</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>API 16+&nbsp;<em>(Reveal animation for API 21 and above, fade animation otherwise)</em></li><li>Two styles</li><li>Option to hide TabLayout automatically when it opens</li><li>Text and animations listeners</li><li>Customization options</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\">\n<p><a href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13675455/46987845-4091c180-d0cc-11e8-8904-87f3c24d4c0a.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7287\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"360\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13675455/46987845-4091c180-d0cc-11e8-8904-87f3c24d4c0a.gif\"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13675455/46987873-60c18080-d0cc-11e8-8d10-2b8cf8a4124b.gif?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7287\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img width=\"360\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13675455/46987873-60c18080-d0cc-11e8-8d10-2b8cf8a4124b.gif\"></a></p>\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7240\">Andrutil</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ShabanKamell/andrutil\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/ShabanKamell/andrutil</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Useful Android Utilities.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Available Utils:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ActivityUtil\nAppUtil\nBackStackUtil\nBottomNavigationViewUtil\nCallback\nDateUtil\nDiskStorageUtil\nFragmentManagerUtil\nFunc\nGsonUtil\nHtmlUtil\nKeyboardUtil\nKeyguardManagerUtil\nLocaleUtil\nMediaPlayerUtil\nObservableUtil\nPackageInfoUtil\nPhoneUtil\nRecyclerViewUtil\nRtlConfigUtil\nServiceUtil\nSpaceItemDecoration\nSystemOverlayUtil\nToastUtil\nWindowUtil\nVectorDrawableUtil\nDrawableUtil</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7244\">DotLoadersPack</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/agrawalsuneet/DotLoadersPack-Android\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/agrawalsuneet/DotLoadersPack-Android</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12999622/39367184-f3bb706a-4a2d-11e8-9120-5027bbef2861.gif\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"20\">\n\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12999622/36224573-f274b956-11bf-11e8-8f97-e4c031959465.gif\">\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7248\">EasyAbout</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/marcoscgdev/EasyAbout\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/marcoscgdev/EasyAbout</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA fully material-designed about fragment for your application.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/marcoscgdev/EasyAbout/master/screenshots/1.png\" alt=\"Sample App\" style=\"max-width:25%;\">\n \n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/marcoscgdev/EasyAbout/master/screenshots/2.png\" alt=\"Sample App\" style=\"max-width:25%;\" hspace=\"20\">\n \n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/marcoscgdev/EasyAbout/master/screenshots/3.png\" alt=\"Sample App\" style=\"max-width:25%;\">\n\n</figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7057\">ScatterImageView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/SIMMORSAL/ScatterImageView\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/SIMMORSAL/ScatterImageView</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nA library that scatters some ImageViews around haphazardly, or orderly\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24822099/42732838-5a9cd2b8-883d-11e8-8463-aefee1f2be11.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/7058\">ReadMoreOption</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/devendroid/ReadMoreOption\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/devendroid/ReadMoreOption</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nConvert your TextView in ExpandableTextView with added options ReadMore/ReadLess.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/devendroid/ReadMoreOption/master/assets/rmo-1.0.0.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/details/1/6996\">TypeWriterView</a></h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/skymansandy/typewriterview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/skymansandy/typewriterview/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>A simple Android library for typewriter like effects</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Features:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Animate contents of textview as if it were typed by a TypeWriter</li><li>Set Animation Text appearance duration</li><li>Set TypeWriter sound effect (With or without sound)</li><li>Set Typing animation listeners (4 available)</li><li>Set all the usual attributes of TextView and style your view.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/skymansandy/typewriterview/master/art/demoTypeWriterView.gif\" alt=\"\" style=\"width:300px;\"></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Github Important Links:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/mmoamenn/AnimationsPlus?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7251\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mmoamenn/AnimationsPlus</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/david-serrano/locationprovider?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7231\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/david-serrano/locationprovider</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/GeorgeArgyrakis/Watermark?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7222\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/GeorgeArgyrakis/Watermark</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Piashsarker/AndroidEasyUtils?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7227\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Piashsarker/AndroidEasyUtils</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/mohammadatif/Animatoo?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7206\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mohammadatif/Animatoo</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/ahmadaghazadeh/CodeEditor?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7185\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/ahmadaghazadeh/CodeEditor</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/SuperRabbitD/NumberPicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7169\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/SuperRabbitD/NumberPicker</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/GrenderG/MarkdownView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7145\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/GrenderG/MarkdownView</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/DMGDesignUK/DmgLocationUtils?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7162\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/DMGDesignUK/DmgLocationUtils</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/armcha/DebugBanner?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7090\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/armcha/DebugBanner</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/mrgames13/DrawingActivity?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7098\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mrgames13/DrawingActivity</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/bitvale/DroidMotion?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7104\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/bitvale/DroidMotion</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyValidation?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7109\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/wajahatkarim3/EasyValidation</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/mjn1369/FieldSetView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7030\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/mjn1369/FieldSetView</a></li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/maayyaannkk/ImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7055\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/maayyaannkk/ImagePicker</a></li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/himangipatel/ImagesPreview?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6979\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/himangipatel/ImagesPreview</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/jaiselrahman/FilePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7002\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/jaiselrahman/FilePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/shagiz/AsyncFilePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=7011\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/shagiz/AsyncFilePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/siralam/BSImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6925\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/siralam/BSImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6935\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/akshay2211/PixImagePicker</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6889\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/nihad92/SwipeableCards</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6850\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/dipanshukr/Viewpager-Transformation</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6807\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/WindSekirun/SectionCalendarView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6779\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Team-Blox/TreeView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6778\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/Angads25/android-toggle</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6782\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/florent37/ShapeOfView</a> </li><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http://github.com/mreram/TicketView?utm_source=android-arsenal.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=6799\" target=\"_blank\">http://github.com/mreram/TicketView</a> </li><li> https://github.com/kevalpatel2106/android-hidden-camera</li><li></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Refrence: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://android-arsenal.com/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://android-arsenal.com/?page=21&amp;sort=created</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Libs And Tools','','inherit','closed','closed','','201-revision-v1','','','2019-02-06 13:00:06','2019-02-06 13:00:06','',201,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/02/06/201-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2019-02-09 08:16:51','2019-02-09 08:16:51','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> There are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely popular and are often used in almost any Android project. Each has different purposes but all of them make life as a developer much more pleasant. The major libraries are listed below in a few categories. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"markdown-header-progressbutton\">ProgressButton</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nShow button with progress bar\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Android Button that morphs into a loading progress bar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Fully customizable in the XML</li><li>Really simple to use.</li><li>Makes your app looks cooler</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/73ab06601fb650fd51fa01781053fde8ff52f9bd/68747470733a2f2f692e737461636b2e696d6775722e636f6d2f38534852312e676966\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Setup\nAdd this <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">to</span> your project build.gradle\n\nallprojects {\n    repositories {\n        maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Dependency\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//before androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButton:1.0\'</span>\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//after androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButtonX:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Usage\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// In your activity_main.xml class:</span>\n\n &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span> layout=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@layout/button_progress\"</span>/&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//  Initialization method</span>\n    btnAction = ProgressButton.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, getActivityRootView())\n                  .setText(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Send Request\"</span>) \n                  .setOnClickListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> View.OnClickListener() {\n                      <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                      <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onClick</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(View v)</span> </span>{ \n                      }\n                  });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Update progress bar methods</span>\n     \n      btnAction.startProgress();\n\n    \n      btnAction.revertSuccessProgress(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ProgressButton.Listener() {\n          @Override\n          public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onAnimationCompleted() {\n          }\n      });\n      \n      btnAction.revertProgress();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CoreLib</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This library contains Android Button which can morph to Circular Progress,    Progress manager used for showing progress bar during making http request with success and failure response handler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link:  <br><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib\" target=\"_blank\">https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>DBInterface</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> SQLite databases is tough while developing. You cannot view the tables, you don\'t know what is getting inserted into the tables and you can\'t update the data and see how your application responds to it. What if you had a database manager like oracle sql developr, mysql work bench for your application\'s SQLite database? This library gives you that. With this library you can manage the database of your android app from the app itself. You can view, insert, delete, update the tables of your app\'s SQLite database from your app. <strong><br>Also Support Android Room Library</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Github link:  <a href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_1\">FirebaseConfig</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setup firebase Remote Config and Crashlist for validating user and crash reporting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link :<br><a href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\">ht</a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\">tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig</a><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Must Have Libraries For Android Developer','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2019-02-09 08:16:51','2019-02-09 08:16:51','',274,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/02/09/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(323,1,'2019-02-09 08:30:07','2019-02-09 08:30:07','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely pop