android:1.2.1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I have included code snippet of a coroutine in action is as below: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Main).launch {\n            toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello it has started\"</span>)\n            delay(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, TimeUnit.SECONDS)\n            textView.text = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"I have changed after 10 seconds\"</span>\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you can see above we used coroutine builders in order to launch and execute a coroutine from a scope which was non-suspending. Easy right!?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Breaking down coroutine builders:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code>launch</code>&nbsp;— This builder simply launches a new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Job</code>&nbsp;object which does not have a result. If you intend to block the current thread, instead of launch you may use&nbsp;<code>runBlocking</code>&nbsp;builder instead.</li><li><code>async</code>&nbsp;— This builder launches new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Deferred</code>&nbsp;type object which may have a result. It is usually used along with&nbsp;<code>await</code>&nbsp;which is a suspending function which can wait for a result without blocking the current thread.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And&nbsp;<code>Dispatchers.Main</code>&nbsp;— this isn’t a coroutine builder however we pass it into our&nbsp;<code>launch</code>&nbsp;builder in order to notify the Android system that we will need to update the UI thread at some point during our coroutine execution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Example : </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> service = RetrofitFactory.makeRetrofitService()\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> response = service.getPosts()\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (response.isSuccessful) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Do something with response e.g show to the UI.</span>\n                    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                        toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Error: <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${response.code()}</span>\"</span>)\n                    }\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: HttpException) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Exception <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${e.message}</span>\"</span>)\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: Throwable) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Ooops: Something else went wrong\"</span>)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1\">https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Kotlin Coroutines and Room','','inherit','closed','closed','','461-revision-v1','','','2019-10-05 08:45:55','2019-10-05 07:45:55','',461,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/05/461-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(465,1,'2019-10-05 08:46:30','2019-10-05 07:46:30','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"969c\">Kotlin Coroutines: A brief intro.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coroutines are a neat new feature of the Kotlin language that allow us to write asynchronous code in a more idiomatic way. — This also means you can write asynchronous code the same way you would normally write synchronous code in your project.<br><br>In order to do asynchronous programming you may have had to use Async Tasks, Threads (which may have been blocking,&nbsp;<em>meh</em>), Callbacks or even RxJava. Using callbacks could have easily ran you into something known as&nbsp;<em>“</em>Callback Hell<em>” — Shoutout to all the JS programmers who’ll read this.&nbsp;</em>And with RxJava, from experience, I noticed that there was quite the learning curve in-order to get an understanding of how to use the various combinators in the case of chaining a few asynchronous calls. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"ff2e\">Coroutines in your Android Project</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kotlin coroutines in Android are very simple to enable in your project. Since they are still in an experimental mode, you may need to also include a few extra steps in your application level&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To begin add the following library to your&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file dependencies:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.2.1\"</span>\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.2.1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I have included code snippet of a coroutine in action is as below: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Main).launch {\n            toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello it has started\"</span>)\n            delay(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, TimeUnit.SECONDS)\n            textView.text = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"I have changed after 10 seconds\"</span>\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you can see above we used coroutine builders in order to launch and execute a coroutine from a scope which was non-suspending. Easy right!?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Breaking down coroutine builders:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code>launch</code>&nbsp;— This builder simply launches a new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Job</code>&nbsp;object which does not have a result. If you intend to block the current thread, instead of launch you may use&nbsp;<code>runBlocking</code>&nbsp;builder instead.</li><li><code>async</code>&nbsp;— This builder launches new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Deferred</code>&nbsp;type object which may have a result. It is usually used along with&nbsp;<code>await</code>&nbsp;which is a suspending function which can wait for a result without blocking the current thread.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And&nbsp;<code>Dispatchers.Main</code>&nbsp;— this isn’t a coroutine builder however we pass it into our&nbsp;<code>launch</code>&nbsp;builder in order to notify the Android system that we will need to update the UI thread at some point during our coroutine execution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Example : </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> service = RetrofitFactory.makeRetrofitService()\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> response = service.getPosts()\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (response.isSuccessful) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Do something with response e.g show to the UI.</span>\n                    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                        toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Error: <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${response.code()}</span>\"</span>)\n                    }\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: HttpException) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Exception <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${e.message}</span>\"</span>)\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: Throwable) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Ooops: Something else went wrong\"</span>)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Kotlin Coroutines and Room','','inherit','closed','closed','','461-revision-v1','','','2019-10-05 08:46:30','2019-10-05 07:46:30','',461,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/05/461-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(466,1,'2019-10-05 08:49:57','2019-10-05 07:49:57','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"969c\">Kotlin Coroutines: A brief intro.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coroutines are a neat new feature of the Kotlin language that allow us to write asynchronous code in a more idiomatic way. — This also means you can write asynchronous code the same way you would normally write synchronous code in your project.<br><br>In order to do asynchronous programming you may have had to use Async Tasks, Threads (which may have been blocking,&nbsp;<em>meh</em>), Callbacks or even RxJava. Using callbacks could have easily ran you into something known as&nbsp;<em>“</em>Callback Hell<em>” — Shoutout to all the JS programmers who’ll read this.&nbsp;</em>And with RxJava, from experience, I noticed that there was quite the learning curve in-order to get an understanding of how to use the various combinators in the case of chaining a few asynchronous calls. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"ff2e\">Coroutines in your Android Project</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kotlin coroutines in Android are very simple to enable in your project. Since they are still in an experimental mode, you may need to also include a few extra steps in your application level&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To begin add the following library to your&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file dependencies:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.2.1\"</span>\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.2.1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I have included code snippet of a coroutine in action is as below: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Main).launch {\n            toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello it has started\"</span>)\n            delay(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, TimeUnit.SECONDS)\n            textView.text = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"I have changed after 10 seconds\"</span>\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you can see above we used coroutine builders in order to launch and execute a coroutine from a scope which was non-suspending. Easy right!?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Breaking down coroutine builders:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code>launch</code>&nbsp;— This builder simply launches a new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Job</code>&nbsp;object which does not have a result. If you intend to block the current thread, instead of launch you may use&nbsp;<code>runBlocking</code>&nbsp;builder instead.</li><li><code>async</code>&nbsp;— This builder launches new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Deferred</code>&nbsp;type object which may have a result. It is usually used along with&nbsp;<code>await</code>&nbsp;which is a suspending function which can wait for a result without blocking the current thread.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And&nbsp;<code>Dispatchers.Main</code>&nbsp;— this isn’t a coroutine builder however we pass it into our&nbsp;<code>launch</code>&nbsp;builder in order to notify the Android system that we will need to update the UI thread at some point during our coroutine execution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Example : </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> service = RetrofitFactory.makeRetrofitService()\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> response = service.getPosts()\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (response.isSuccessful) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Do something with response e.g show to the UI.</span>\n                    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                        toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Error: <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${response.code()}</span>\"</span>)\n                    }\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: HttpException) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Exception <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${e.message}</span>\"</span>)\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: Throwable) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Ooops: Something else went wrong\"</span>)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1\" target=\"_blank\">https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb\">https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Kotlin Coroutines and Room','','inherit','closed','closed','','461-revision-v1','','','2019-10-05 08:49:57','2019-10-05 07:49:57','',461,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/05/461-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(467,1,'2019-10-05 08:58:44','2019-10-05 07:58:44','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"969c\">Kotlin Coroutines: A brief intro.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coroutines are a neat new feature of the Kotlin language that allow us to write asynchronous code in a more idiomatic way. — This also means you can write asynchronous code the same way you would normally write synchronous code in your project.<br><br>In order to do asynchronous programming you may have had to use Async Tasks, Threads (which may have been blocking,&nbsp;<em>meh</em>), Callbacks or even RxJava. Using callbacks could have easily ran you into something known as&nbsp;<em>“</em>Callback Hell<em>” — Shoutout to all the JS programmers who’ll read this.&nbsp;</em>And with RxJava, from experience, I noticed that there was quite the learning curve in-order to get an understanding of how to use the various combinators in the case of chaining a few asynchronous calls. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"ff2e\">Coroutines in your Android Project</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kotlin coroutines in Android are very simple to enable in your project. Since they are still in an experimental mode, you may need to also include a few extra steps in your application level&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To begin add the following library to your&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file dependencies:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.2.1\"</span>\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.2.1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I have included code snippet of a coroutine in action is as below: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Main).launch {\n            toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello it has started\"</span>)\n            delay(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, TimeUnit.SECONDS)\n            textView.text = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"I have changed after 10 seconds\"</span>\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you can see above we used coroutine builders in order to launch and execute a coroutine from a scope which was non-suspending. Easy right!?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Breaking down coroutine builders:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code>launch</code>&nbsp;— This builder simply launches a new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Job</code>&nbsp;object which does not have a result. If you intend to block the current thread, instead of launch you may use&nbsp;<code>runBlocking</code>&nbsp;builder instead.</li><li><code>async</code>&nbsp;— This builder launches new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Deferred</code>&nbsp;type object which may have a result. It is usually used along with&nbsp;<code>await</code>&nbsp;which is a suspending function which can wait for a result without blocking the current thread.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And&nbsp;<code>Dispatchers.Main</code>&nbsp;— this isn’t a coroutine builder however we pass it into our&nbsp;<code>launch</code>&nbsp;builder in order to notify the Android system that we will need to update the UI thread at some point during our coroutine execution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Example : </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> service = RetrofitFactory.makeRetrofitService()\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> response = service.getPosts()\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (response.isSuccessful) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Do something with response e.g show to the UI.</span>\n                    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                        toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Error: <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${response.code()}</span>\"</span>)\n                    }\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: HttpException) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Exception <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${e.message}</span>\"</span>)\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: Throwable) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Ooops: Something else went wrong\"</span>)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/how-to-make-sense-of-kotlin-coroutines-b666c7151b93\">https://proandroiddev.com/how-to-make-sense-of-kotlin-coroutines-b666c7151b93</a> </li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1\" target=\"_blank\">https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1</a></li><li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb\">https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Kotlin Coroutines and Room','','inherit','closed','closed','','461-revision-v1','','','2019-10-05 08:58:44','2019-10-05 07:58:44','',461,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/05/461-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(468,1,'2019-10-07 08:32:16','2019-10-07 07:32:16','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"969c\">Kotlin Coroutines: A brief intro.</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coroutines are a neat new feature of the Kotlin language that allow us to write asynchronous code in a more idiomatic way. — This also means you can write asynchronous code the same way you would normally write synchronous code in your project.<br><br>In order to do asynchronous programming you may have had to use Async Tasks, Threads (which may have been blocking,&nbsp;<em>meh</em>), Callbacks or even RxJava. Using callbacks could have easily ran you into something known as&nbsp;<em>“</em>Callback Hell<em>” — Shoutout to all the JS programmers who’ll read this.&nbsp;</em>And with RxJava, from experience, I noticed that there was quite the learning curve in-order to get an understanding of how to use the various combinators in the case of chaining a few asynchronous calls. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"ff2e\">Coroutines in your Android Project</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kotlin coroutines in Android are very simple to enable in your project. Since they are still in an experimental mode, you may need to also include a few extra steps in your application level&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To begin add the following library to your&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;file dependencies:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.2.1\"</span>\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.2.1\"</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span><span class=\"hljs-attr\">...</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I have included code snippet of a coroutine in action is as below: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.Main).launch {\n            toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello it has started\"</span>)\n            delay(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>, TimeUnit.SECONDS)\n            textView.text = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"I have changed after 10 seconds\"</span>\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you can see above we used coroutine builders in order to launch and execute a coroutine from a scope which was non-suspending. Easy right!?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Breaking down coroutine builders:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code>launch</code>&nbsp;— This builder simply launches a new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Job</code>&nbsp;object which does not have a result. If you intend to block the current thread, instead of launch you may use&nbsp;<code>runBlocking</code>&nbsp;builder instead.</li><li><code>async</code>&nbsp;— This builder launches new coroutine and returns a reference to it as a&nbsp;<code>Deferred</code>&nbsp;type object which may have a result. It is usually used along with&nbsp;<code>await</code>&nbsp;which is a suspending function which can wait for a result without blocking the current thread.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And&nbsp;<code>Dispatchers.Main</code>&nbsp;— this isn’t a coroutine builder however we pass it into our&nbsp;<code>launch</code>&nbsp;builder in order to notify the Android system that we will need to update the UI thread at some point during our coroutine execution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Example : </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MainActivity</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span></span>() {\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">override</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onCreate</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(savedInstanceState: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span>?)</span></span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(savedInstanceState)\n        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> service = RetrofitFactory.makeRetrofitService()\n        CoroutineScope(Dispatchers.IO).launch {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">val</span> response = service.getPosts()\n            withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (response.isSuccessful) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Do something with response e.g show to the UI.</span>\n                    } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                        toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Error: <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${response.code()}</span>\"</span>)\n                    }\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: HttpException) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Exception <span class=\"hljs-subst\">${e.message}</span>\"</span>)\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (e: Throwable) {\n                    toast(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Ooops: Something else went wrong\"</span>)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/how-to-make-sense-of-kotlin-coroutines-b666c7151b93\">https://proandroiddev.com/how-to-make-sense-of-kotlin-coroutines-b666c7151b93</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://medium.com/androiddevelopers/coroutines-on-android-part-iii-real-work-2ba8a2ec2f45\">https://medium.com/androiddevelopers/coroutines-on-android-part-iii-real-work-2ba8a2ec2f45</a> </li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1\" target=\"_blank\">https://proandroiddev.com/kotlin-coroutines-for-asynchronous-programming-and-more-1892db686b1</a></li><li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb\">https://medium.com/@marcogomiero/a-journey-from-async-task-to-kotlin-coroutines-735c273d76cb</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','Kotlin Coroutines and Room','','inherit','closed','closed','','461-revision-v1','','','2019-10-07 08:32:16','2019-10-07 07:32:16','',461,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/07/461-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(469,1,'2019-10-11 07:51:41','2019-10-11 06:51:41','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The DayNight functionality in AppCompat allows your app to easily switch between a dark ⚫ and light ⚪ theme. This has many benefits for your users, from saving power on OLED displays, to increasing usability for people with reduced-vision, and more. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"97e1\">setDefaultNightMode</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first API we provide to do that is&nbsp;<code>AppCompatDelegate.<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/appcompat/app/AppCompatDelegate#setDefaultNightMode(int)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">setDefaultNightMode()</a></code>, which takes one of the follow values:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><code><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/appcompat/app/AppCompatDelegate.html#MODE_NIGHT_NO\" target=\"_blank\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</a></code>. Always use the day (light) theme.</li><li><code><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/appcompat/app/AppCompatDelegate.html#MODE_NIGHT_YES\" target=\"_blank\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</a></code>. Always use the night (dark) theme.</li><li><code><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/appcompat/app/AppCompatDelegate.html#MODE_NIGHT_FOLLOW_SYSTEM\" target=\"_blank\">MODE_NIGHT_FOLLOW_SYSTEM</a></code>&nbsp;<em>(default)</em>. This setting follows the system’s setting, which on Android Q and above is a system setting (more on this below).</li><li><code>MODE_NIGHT_AUTO_BATTERY</code>. Changes to dark when the device has its ‘Battery Saver’ feature enabled, light otherwise.<br>✨<strong><em>New in v1.1.0-alpha03.</em></strong></li><li><code>MODE_NIGHT_AUTO_TIME</code>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<code><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/appcompat/app/AppCompatDelegate.html#MODE_NIGHT_AUTO\" target=\"_blank\">MODE_NIGHT_AUTO</a></code>. Changes between day/night based on the time of day.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The method is static so you can call it at any time. The value you set is&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;persisted across process starts though, therefore you need to set it every time your app process is started. I recommend setting it in your application class (if you have one) like so: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    public <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyApplication</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Application</span> </span>{\n\n        public void onCreate() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate();\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppPreferences</span>.isDayMode(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>)) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</span>);\n            } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span>);\n            }\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Previously you could do the following quite happily, without AppCompat needing to recreate the Activity: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">public <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyActivity</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Activity</span> </span>{\n    \n    public void onCreate(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span> icicle) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(icicle);\n        getDelegate().setLocalNightMode(\n                <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span>);\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"4e1e\">In-app setting</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is recommended to provide a way for the user to override the default theme in your app. The recommended options and strings are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>‘Light’ (<code>MODE_NIGHT_NO</code>)</li><li>‘Dark’ (<code>MODE_NIGHT_YES</code>)</li><li>‘Set by Battery Saver’ (<code>MODE_NIGHT_AUTO_BATTERY</code>).<em><br>Only show on Android Pie and below. This should be your app’s default when shown.</em></li><li>‘Use system default’ (<code>MODE_NIGHT_FOLLOW_SYSTEM</code>).<br><em>Only show on Android Q and above. This should be your app’s default when shown.</em></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A common way to do to implement would be via a&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/settings/components-and-attributes\" target=\"_blank\">ListPreference</a>, calling to&nbsp;<code>setDefaultNightMode()</code>&nbsp;when the value changes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"6eb8\">Using your own resources for dark/light</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AppCompat in simple terms is just enabling the use of the&nbsp;<code>night</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code>notnight</code>&nbsp;resource qualifiers. These have actually been available in the platform since API 8, but were previously only used in very specific scenarios.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Under the hood&nbsp;<code>Theme.AppCompat.DayNight</code>&nbsp;is implemented as so:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>res/values/themes.xml</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">&lt;style name=\"Theme.AppCompat.DayNight\" <br>       parent=\"Theme.AppCompat.Light\" /&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>res/values-night/themes.xml</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">&lt;style name=\"Theme.AppCompat.DayNight\" <br>       parent=\"Theme.AppCompat\" /&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This means that you can also provide alternative resources for your light and dark UIs. Just use the&nbsp;<code>-<strong>night</strong></code>&nbsp;qualifier on your resource folders:&nbsp;<code>drawable-night</code>,&nbsp;<code>values-night</code>, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Example:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In your Application class</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    public <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyApplication</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Application</span> </span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">protected</span> void attachBaseContext(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Context</span> base) {\n            initTheme(base);\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.attachBaseContext(base);  \n        }\n\n        public void initTheme(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Context</span> context) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (!<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppPreferences</span>.isDayMode(context)) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span>);\n            } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</span>);\n            }\n        } \n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In your Activity class</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    public <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyActivity</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Activity</span> </span>{\n\n        public void onCreate(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Bundle</span> icicle) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onCreate(icicle);\n            setDayNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppPreferences</span>.isDayMode(activity));\n        }\n\n        public void setDayNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Context</span> context, boolean isDayMode) { \n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (context instanceof <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span>) {\n                ((<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatActivity</span>) context).getDelegate().setLocalNightMode( isDayMode\n                        ? <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</span> : <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span> );\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (isDayMode) {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</span>);\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span>);\n                }\n            } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (isDayMode) {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_NO</span>);\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.setDefaultNightMode(<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">AppCompatDelegate</span>.<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">MODE_NIGHT_YES</span>);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>res/values/colors.xml</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"xml\"><span class=\"php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">&lt;?</span>xml version=<span clas