he description of the program, Java Android code, explanation as well as output of the program. <br>Below are Android Code Examples, Tutorials and projects to make android applications:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Android TextView : “Do not concatenate text displayed with setText”</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> helloWorld = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"World\"</span>);\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> count = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world_count, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>);\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> totalCount = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Total : $count\"</span>;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> world <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">position</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'$s\'</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;Hello - %s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> hello world\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;%<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s - %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">numeric</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">value</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world_count\"</span>&gt;%d Item Selected&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    // example\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"welcome_messages\"</span>&gt;Hello, %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s! You have %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$d <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> messages.&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">using</span> getString(R.string.welcome_message, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Test\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t get confused with&nbsp;<strong>%1$s</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>%2$d</strong>&nbsp;in the accepted answer.Here is a few extra information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The format specifiers can be of the following syntax:</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>%[<code>argument_index</code>$]<code>format_specifier</code></p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The optional&nbsp;<strong>argument_index</strong>&nbsp;is specified as a number ending with a “$” after the “%” and selects the specified argument in the argument list. The first argument is referenced by&nbsp;<strong>\"1$\"</strong>, the second by&nbsp;<strong>\"2$\"</strong>, etc.</li><li>The required&nbsp;<strong>format specifier</strong>&nbsp;is a character indicating how the argument should be formatted. The set of valid conversions for a given argument depends on the argument\'s&nbsp;<strong>data type.</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_3\">How can I show the shadow only on the bottom side of the layout </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nAn important thing here is the attribute&nbsp;<code>outlineProvider</code>, that is required to make the outer Layout cast a shadow even without having a background set.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"xml\"><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span> \n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_width</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"match_parent\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_height</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"wrap_content\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:background</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@android:color/white\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:elevation</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"2dp\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:outlineProvider</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"bounds\"</span> &gt;</span>\n <span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span>&gt;</span>\n</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Validate URL</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">boolean</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">isValidURL</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String urlStr)</span> </span>{\n          <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>  Patterns.WEB_URL.matcher(urlStr).matches();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>UI post delay by time interval using Handler</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler().postDelayed(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{ \n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// write your code here</span>\n            }\n        }, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">400</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Useful for small background tasks</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//        Declear in class </span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> Handler <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span> = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Thread(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Try to sleep the thread for 20 milliseconds</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    Thread.sleep(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">20</span>);  <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//3 seconds</span>\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (InterruptedException e) {\n                    e.printStackTrace();\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Update the progress bar</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span>.post(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//                             updateUi()</span>\n                    }\n                });\n            }\n        }).start(); <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Start the operation</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>How do I escape a single quote in SQL Query</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">word</span>.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">replace</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\'\"</span>)</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Http request using webView  </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> void callWebviewAuth() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web = (WebView)findViewById();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.getSettings().setJavaScriptEnabled(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearCache(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearHistory(); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.loadUrl(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"https://www.facebook.com/v2.6/dialog/oauth?redirect_uri=fb464891386855067%3A%2F%2Fauthorize%2F&amp;scope=user_birthday,user_photos,user_education_history,email,user_relationship_details,user_friends,user_work_history,user_likes&amp;response_type=token%2Csigned_request&amp;client_id=464891386855067\"</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient(){\n            String authCode;\n            boolean authComplete = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>;\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onFormResubmission(WebView webView, Message message, Message message2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onFormResubmission(webView, message, message2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onLoadResource(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onLoadResource(webView, string2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*\n             * Enabled aggressive block sorting\n             */</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageFinished(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageFinished(webView, string2); \n                Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1 = string2;\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"access_token=\"</span>) &amp;&amp; !<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.authComplete) {\n                     \n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (!string2.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"error=access_denied\"</span>)) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    {\n                        \n                        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageStarted(WebView webView, String string2, Bitmap bitmap) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageStarted(webView, string2, bitmap);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4388992/key-hash-for-android-facebook-app\">Key hash for Android-&nbsp;Facebook&nbsp;Login</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the steps-</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Download openssl from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8k_WIN32.zip\"><strong>Google code</strong></a>&nbsp;(If you have a 64 bit machine you must&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8e_X64.zip&amp;can=2&amp;q=\"><strong>download openssl-0.9.8e X64</strong></a>&nbsp;not the latest version)</li><li>Extract it. create a folder- OpenSSL in C:/ and copy the extracted code here.</li><li>detect debug.keystore file path. If u didn\'t find, then do a search in C:/ and use the Path in the command in next step.</li><li>open cmd and change directory cd \"C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_191\\bin\" </li><li>run keytool command mentioned below.<ul><li>it will ask for password, put android</li><li>that\'s all. u will get a key-hash </li></ul></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">keytool -exportcert -alias androiddebugkey -keystore \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">Users</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">kkk</span></span>.android<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">debug</span></span>.keystore\" | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" sha1 -binary | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" base64</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Pass data in fragment using Arguments</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThe underlying Binder transaction buffer has a limited fixed size, currently 1Mb, which is shared by all transactions in progress for the process.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> static Fragment newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data1, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data2, ArrayList&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>) {\n        Fragment fragment = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Fragment(); \n        Bundle bundle = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Bundle();\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data1\"</span>, data1);\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data2\"</span>, data2);\n        bundle.putParcelableArrayList(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"list\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>);\n        fragment.setArguments(bundle); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> fragment;\n    }\n    \n    @Override\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onCreate(@Nullable Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span>(getArguments()!=<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) {\n            data1 = getArguments().getString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data1\"</span>);\n            data2 = getArguments().getString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data2\"</span>);\n            <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> = getArguments().getParcelableArrayList(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"list\"</span>);\n        } \n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Useful Codes','','inherit','closed','closed','','278-revision-v1','','','2019-10-12 08:02:11','2019-10-12 07:02:11','',278,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/12/278-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(475,1,'2019-10-18 09:05:46','2019-10-18 08:05:46','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Save data in a local database using Room</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room provides an abstraction layer over SQLite to allow fluent database access while harnessing the full power of SQLite.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are 3 major components in Room:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Database:</strong>&nbsp;Contains the database holder and serves as the main access point for the underlying connection to your app\'s persisted, relational data.The class that\'s annotated with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Database.html\"><code>@Database</code></a>&nbsp;should satisfy the following conditions:<ul><li>Be an abstract class that extends&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/RoomDatabase.html\"><code>RoomDatabase</code></a>.</li><li>Include the list of entities associated with the database within the annotation.</li><li>Contain an abstract method that has 0 arguments and returns the class that is annotated with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Dao.html\"><code>@Dao</code></a>.At runtime, you can acquire an instance of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Database.html\"><code>Database</code></a>&nbsp;by calling&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Room.html#databaseBuilder(android.content.Context,%20java.lang.Class%3CT%3E,%20java.lang.String)\"><code>Room.databaseBuilder()</code></a>&nbsp;or<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Room.html#inMemoryDatabaseBuilder(android.content.Context,%20java.lang.Class%3CT%3E)\"><code>Room.inMemoryDatabaseBuilder()</code></a>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Entity:</strong>&nbsp;Represents a table within the database.</li><li><strong>DAO:</strong>&nbsp;Contains the methods used for accessing the database.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The following code snippet contains a sample database configuration with one entity and one DAO:\\</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Entity</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">User</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@PrimaryKey</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> uid;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"first_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String firstName;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String lastName;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>UserDao</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserDao</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">getAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE uid IN (:userIds)\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadAllByIds</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span>[] userIds)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE first_name LIKE :first AND \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name LIKE :last LIMIT 1\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">User <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findByName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String first, String last)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">delete</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user)</span></span>;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AppDatabase</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Database</span>(entities = {User.class}, version = <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>)\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">AppDatabase</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">RoomDatabase</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> UserDao <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">userDao</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After creating the files above, you get an instance of the created database using the following code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">AppDatabase db = Room.databaseBuilder(getApplicationContext(),\n        AppDatabase.class, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"database-name\"</span>).build();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#d9edf9\"} -->\n<p style=\"background-color:#d9edf9\" class=\"has-background\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>If your app runs in a single process, you should follow the singleton design pattern when instantiating an&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;object. Each&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/RoomDatabase.html\"><code>RoomDatabase</code></a>&nbsp;instance is fairly expensive, and you rarely need access to multiple instances within a single process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#d9edf9\"} -->\n<p style=\"background-color:#d9edf9\" class=\"has-background\">If your app runs in multiple processes, include&nbsp;<code>enableMultiInstanceInvalidation()</code>&nbsp;in your database builder invocation. That way, when you have an instance of&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;in each process, you can invalidate the shared database file in one process, and this invalidation automatically propagates to the instances of&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;within other processes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Database Queries</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Insert</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you create a DAO method and annotate it with <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Insert.html\">@Insert</a>, Room generates an implementation that inserts all parameters into the database in a single transaction.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>(onConflict = OnConflictStrategy.REPLACE)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertBothUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user1, User user2)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertUsersAndFriends</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user, List&lt;User&gt; friends)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Update</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Update.html\">Update</a> convenience method modifies a set of entities, given as parameters, in the database. It uses a query that matches against the primary key of each entity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Update</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">updateUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Delete</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Delete.html\">Delete</a> convenience method removes a set of entities, given as parameters, from the database. It uses the primary keys to find the entities to delete.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Query for information</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Query.html\">@Query</a> is the main annotation used in DAO classes. It allows you to perform read/write operations on a database. Each <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Query.html\">@Query</a> method is verified at compile time, so if there is a problem with the query, a compilation error occurs instead of a runtime failure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room also verifies the return value of the query such that if the name of the field in the returned object doesn\'t match the corresponding column names in the query response, Room alerts you in one of the following two ways:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>It gives a warning if only some field names match.</li><li>It gives an error if no field names match.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsers();\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Passing parameters into the query</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age &gt; :minAge\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsersOlderThan(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge);\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also pass multiple parameters or reference them multiple times in a query, as shown in the following code snippet:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age BETWEEN :minAge AND :maxAge\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsersBetweenAges(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> maxAge);\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE first_name LIKE :search \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"OR last_name LIKE :search\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findUserWithName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String search)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Returning subsets of columns</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">NameTuple</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"first_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String firstName;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String lastName;\n\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;NameTuple&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadFullName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Passing a collection of arguments</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some of your queries might require you to pass in a variable number of parameters, with the exact number of parameters not known until runtime. For example, you might want to retrieve information about all users from a subset of regions. Room understands when a parameter represents a collection and automatically expands it at runtime based on the number of parameters provided.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user WHERE region IN (:regions)\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;NameTuple&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadUsersFromRegions</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;String&gt; regions)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Observable queries</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When performing queries, you\'ll often want your app\'s UI to update automatically when the data changes. To achieve this, use a return value of type <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/lifecycle/LiveData.html\">LiveData</a> in your query method description. Room generates all necessary code to update the <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/lifecycle/LiveData.html\">LiveData</a> when the database is updated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user WHERE region IN (:regions)\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> LiveData&lt;List&lt;User&gt;&gt; loadUsersFromRegionsSync(List&lt;String&gt; regions);\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Reactive queries with RxJava</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room provides the following support for return values of RxJava2 types:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>@Query methods: Room supports return values of type <a href=\"http://www.reactive-streams.org/reactive-streams-1.0.1-javadoc/org/reactivestreams/Publisher.html\">Publisher</a>, <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/2.x/javadoc/io/reactivex/Flowable.html\">Flowable</a>, and<a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/2.x/javadoc/io/reactivex/Observable.html\">Observable</a>.</li><li>@Insert, @Update, and @Delete methods: Room 2.1.0 and higher supports return values of type<a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Completable.html\">Completable</a>, <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Single.html\">Single&lt;T&gt;</a>, and <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Maybe.html\">Maybe&lt;T&gt;</a>.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To use this functionality, include the latest version of the <strong>rxjava2</strong> artifact in your app\'s build.gradle file:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">app/build.gradle</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.room:room-rxjava2:2.1.0-alpha02\'</span>\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * from user where id = :id LIMIT 1\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Flowable&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadUserById</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> id)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Emits the number of users added to the database.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Maybe&lt;Integer&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertLargeNumberOfUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;User&gt; users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Makes sure that the operation finishes successfully.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Completable <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertLargeNumberOfUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/* Emits the number of users removed from the database. Always emits at\n       least one user. */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Single&lt;Integer&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;User&gt; users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Direct cursor access</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your app\'s logic requires direct access to the return rows, you can return a <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/Cursor.html\">Cursor</a> object from your queries, as shown in the following code snippet:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age &gt; :minAge LIMIT 5\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Cursor <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadRawUsersOlderThan</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Querying multiple tables</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM book \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"INNER JOIN loan ON loan.book_id = book.id \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"INNER JOIN user ON user.id = loan.user_id \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"WHERE user.name LIKE :userName\"</span>)\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;Book&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findBooksBorrowedByNameSync</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String userName)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also return POJOs from these queries. For example, you can write a query that loads a user and their pet\'s name as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT user.name AS userName, pet.name AS petName \"</span> +\n          <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"FROM user, pet \"</span> +\n          <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"WHERE user.id = pet.user_id\"</span>)\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> LiveData&lt;List&lt;UserPet&gt;&gt; loadUserAndPetNames();\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// You can also define this class in a separate file, as long as you add the</span>\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// \"public\" access modifier.</span>\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserPet</span> </span>{\n       <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String userName;\n       <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String petName;\n   }\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Best way to Run Room queries in background threads</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Never use&nbsp;<em>allowMainThreadQueries()&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might be referring&nbsp;to many blogs and medium posts for implementing Room other than official Android documentation. One thing I found in them was the use of&nbsp;<em>allowMainThreadQueries()</em>&nbsp;method! You should never ever use this method for building your database class. You have to use another thread for all database queries (Especially for queries with insert/update/delete).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Never use AsyncTask.class for your queries</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I have proposed the ban on allowMainThreadQueries(), You may be thinking of implementing an AsycTask class for your database queries. Sometimes AsyncTask also fails to make your DB queries. Once you go through the AsyncTask documentation you can find something like <a href=\"https://www.techeos.com/posts/android-workmanager-api-finally/\">this</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>AsyncTasks should ideally be used for short operations (a few seconds at the most.) If you need to keep threads running for long periods of time, it is highly recommended you use the various APIs provided by&nbsp;</em>the package<em><code>java.util.concurrent</code></em><em>&nbsp;such&nbsp;</em>as,<em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/Executor.html\">Executor</a></code></em><em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/ThreadPoolExecutor.html\">ThreadPoolExecutor</a></code>&nbsp;</em>and.<em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/FutureTask.html\">FutureTask</a></code></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So you must move your queries to any services or any other thread maintainers. A simple example using Executor.class is given below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Executor myExecutor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();\nmyExecutor.execute<span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(() -&gt; {\n    myDao.insert(userObject);\n})</span>;</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Use&nbsp;<em>synchronized</em>&nbsp;for accessing database</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Usually, you only need one instance of the Room database for the whole app. In order to maintain this implementation, You have to create a singleton instance which gives the database instance using the synchronized method. So that, You can ensure the concurrent access of database is synchronized along the whole thread.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">//Sample database<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>class.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">\nstatic</span> UserDatabase INSTANCE;\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">\npublic</span><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> static</span> UserDatabase getDatabase(final Context context) {\n   <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(INSTANCE == null) {\n        synchronized (UserDatabase.class) {\n           <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(INSTANCE == null) {\n                INSTANCE = Room.databaseBuilder(context.getApplicationContext(),\n                        UserDatabase.class, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"database_name\"</span>)\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">                        .build</span>();\n\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> return </span>INSTANCE;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bundle your queries together in DAO interface</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your query abstract function uses another&nbsp;two queries function, You can wrap them together in your DAO class. So that you can avoid boilerplate codes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserDao</span> </span>{\n    \n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Bundles to calls together here.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Transaction</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">open</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">updateData</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(users: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">User</span>&gt;)</span></span> {\n        deleteAllUsers()\n        insertAll(users)\n    }\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(users: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">User</span>&gt;)</span></span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query(<span class=\"hljs-meta-string\">\"DELETE FROM Users\"</span>)</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteAllUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Reference:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room/\">https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room/</a>&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Room Database','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2019-10-18 09:05:46','2019-10-18 08:05:46','',92,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/18/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(476,1,'2019-10-18 09:06:30','2019-10-18 08:06:30','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Save data in a local database using Room</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room provides an abstraction layer over SQLite to allow fluent database access while harnessing the full power of SQLite.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are 3 major components in Room:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Database:</strong>&nbsp;Contains the database holder and serves as the main access point for the underlying connection to your app\'s persisted, relational data.The class that\'s annotated with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Database.html\"><code>@Database</code></a>&nbsp;should satisfy the following conditions:<ul><li>Be an abstract class that extends&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/RoomDatabase.html\"><code>RoomDatabase</code></a>.</li><li>Include the list of entities associated with the database within the annotation.</li><li>Contain an abstract method that has 0 arguments and returns the class that is annotated with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Dao.html\"><code>@Dao</code></a>.At runtime, you can acquire an instance of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Database.html\"><code>Database</code></a>&nbsp;by calling&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Room.html#databaseBuilder(android.content.Context,%20java.lang.Class%3CT%3E,%20java.lang.String)\"><code>Room.databaseBuilder()</code></a>&nbsp;or<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Room.html#inMemoryDatabaseBuilder(android.content.Context,%20java.lang.Class%3CT%3E)\"><code>Room.inMemoryDatabaseBuilder()</code></a>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Entity:</strong>&nbsp;Represents a table within the database.</li><li><strong>DAO:</strong>&nbsp;Contains the methods used for accessing the database.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The following code snippet contains a sample database configuration with one entity and one DAO:\\</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Entity</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">User</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@PrimaryKey</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> uid;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"first_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String firstName;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String lastName;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>UserDao</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserDao</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">getAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE uid IN (:userIds)\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadAllByIds</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span>[] userIds)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE first_name LIKE :first AND \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name LIKE :last LIMIT 1\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\">User <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findByName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String first, String last)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">delete</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user)</span></span>;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AppDatabase</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Database</span>(entities = {User.class}, version = <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>)\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">AppDatabase</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">extends</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">RoomDatabase</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> UserDao <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">userDao</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After creating the files above, you get an instance of the created database using the following code:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">AppDatabase db = Room.databaseBuilder(getApplicationContext(),\n        AppDatabase.class, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"database-name\"</span>).build();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#d9edf9\"} -->\n<p style=\"background-color:#d9edf9\" class=\"has-background\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>If your app runs in a single process, you should follow the singleton design pattern when instantiating an&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;object. Each&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/RoomDatabase.html\"><code>RoomDatabase</code></a>&nbsp;instance is fairly expensive, and you rarely need access to multiple instances within a single process.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#d9edf9\"} -->\n<p style=\"background-color:#d9edf9\" class=\"has-background\">If your app runs in multiple processes, include&nbsp;<code>enableMultiInstanceInvalidation()</code>&nbsp;in your database builder invocation. That way, when you have an instance of&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;in each process, you can invalidate the shared database file in one process, and this invalidation automatically propagates to the instances of&nbsp;<code>AppDatabase</code>&nbsp;within other processes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Database Queries</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Insert</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you create a DAO method and annotate it with <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Insert.html\">@Insert</a>, Room generates an implementation that inserts all parameters into the database in a single transaction.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>(onConflict = OnConflictStrategy.REPLACE)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertBothUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user1, User user2)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertUsersAndFriends</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User user, List&lt;User&gt; friends)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Update</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Update.html\">Update</a> convenience method modifies a set of entities, given as parameters, in the database. It uses a query that matches against the primary key of each entity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Update</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">updateUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Delete</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Delete.html\">Delete</a> convenience method removes a set of entities, given as parameters, from the database. It uses the primary keys to find the entities to delete.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Query for information</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Query.html\">@Query</a> is the main annotation used in DAO classes. It allows you to perform read/write operations on a database. Each <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/room/Query.html\">@Query</a> method is verified at compile time, so if there is a problem with the query, a compilation error occurs instead of a runtime failure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room also verifies the return value of the query such that if the name of the field in the returned object doesn\'t match the corresponding column names in the query response, Room alerts you in one of the following two ways:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>It gives a warning if only some field names match.</li><li>It gives an error if no field names match.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsers();\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Passing parameters into the query</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age &gt; :minAge\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsersOlderThan(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge);\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also pass multiple parameters or reference them multiple times in a query, as shown in the following code snippet:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age BETWEEN :minAge AND :maxAge\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> User[] loadAllUsersBetweenAges(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> maxAge);\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE first_name LIKE :search \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"OR last_name LIKE :search\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findUserWithName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String search)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Returning subsets of columns</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">NameTuple</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"first_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String firstName;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@ColumnInfo</span>(name = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"last_name\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String lastName;\n\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user\"</span>)\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;NameTuple&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadFullName</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Passing a collection of arguments</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some of your queries might require you to pass in a variable number of parameters, with the exact number of parameters not known until runtime. For example, you might want to retrieve information about all users from a subset of regions. Room understands when a parameter represents a collection and automatically expands it at runtime based on the number of parameters provided.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user WHERE region IN (:regions)\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;NameTuple&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadUsersFromRegions</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;String&gt; regions)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Observable queries</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When performing queries, you\'ll often want your app\'s UI to update automatically when the data changes. To achieve this, use a return value of type <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/lifecycle/LiveData.html\">LiveData</a> in your query method description. Room generates all necessary code to update the <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/androidx/lifecycle/LiveData.html\">LiveData</a> when the database is updated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT first_name, last_name FROM user WHERE region IN (:regions)\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> LiveData&lt;List&lt;User&gt;&gt; loadUsersFromRegionsSync(List&lt;String&gt; regions);\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Reactive queries with RxJava</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Room provides the following support for return values of RxJava2 types:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>@Query methods: Room supports return values of type <a href=\"http://www.reactive-streams.org/reactive-streams-1.0.1-javadoc/org/reactivestreams/Publisher.html\">Publisher</a>, <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/2.x/javadoc/io/reactivex/Flowable.html\">Flowable</a>, and<a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/2.x/javadoc/io/reactivex/Observable.html\">Observable</a>.</li><li>@Insert, @Update, and @Delete methods: Room 2.1.0 and higher supports return values of type<a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Completable.html\">Completable</a>, <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Single.html\">Single&lt;T&gt;</a>, and <a href=\"http://reactivex.io/RxJava/javadoc/io/reactivex/Maybe.html\">Maybe&lt;T&gt;</a>.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To use this functionality, include the latest version of the <strong>rxjava2</strong> artifact in your app\'s build.gradle file:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">app/build.gradle</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.room:room-rxjava2:2.1.0-alpha02\'</span>\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * from user where id = :id LIMIT 1\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Flowable&lt;User&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadUserById</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> id)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Emits the number of users added to the database.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Maybe&lt;Integer&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertLargeNumberOfUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;User&gt; users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Makes sure that the operation finishes successfully.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Completable <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertLargeNumberOfUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(User... users)</span></span>;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/* Emits the number of users removed from the database. Always emits at\n       least one user. */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Delete</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Single&lt;Integer&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(List&lt;User&gt; users)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Direct cursor access</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your app\'s logic requires direct access to the return rows, you can return a <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/Cursor.html\">Cursor</a> object from your queries, as shown in the following code snippet:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM user WHERE age &gt; :minAge LIMIT 5\"</span>)\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> Cursor <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">loadRawUsersOlderThan</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">int</span> minAge)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Querying multiple tables</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT * FROM book \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"INNER JOIN loan ON loan.book_id = book.id \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"INNER JOIN user ON user.id = loan.user_id \"</span> +\n           <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"WHERE user.name LIKE :userName\"</span>)\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> List&lt;Book&gt; <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">findBooksBorrowedByNameSync</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String userName)</span></span>;\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also return POJOs from these queries. For example, you can write a query that loads a user and their pet\'s name as follows:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">interface</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">MyDao</span> </span>{\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SELECT user.name AS userName, pet.name AS petName \"</span> +\n          <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"FROM user, pet \"</span> +\n          <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"WHERE user.id = pet.user_id\"</span>)\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> LiveData&lt;List&lt;UserPet&gt;&gt; loadUserAndPetNames();\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// You can also define this class in a separate file, as long as you add the</span>\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// \"public\" access modifier.</span>\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserPet</span> </span>{\n       <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String userName;\n       <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> String petName;\n   }\n\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Best way to Run Room queries in background threads</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Never use&nbsp;<em>allowMainThreadQueries()&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might be referring&nbsp;to many blogs and medium posts for implementing Room other than official Android documentation. One thing I found in them was the use of&nbsp;<em>allowMainThreadQueries()</em>&nbsp;method! You should never ever use this method for building your database class. You have to use another thread for all database queries (Especially for queries with insert/update/delete).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Never use AsyncTask.class for your queries</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I have proposed the ban on allowMainThreadQueries(), You may be thinking of implementing an AsycTask class for your database queries. Sometimes AsyncTask also fails to make your DB queries. Once you go through the AsyncTask documentation you can find something like <a href=\"https://www.techeos.com/posts/android-workmanager-api-finally/\">this</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>AsyncTasks should ideally be used for short operations (a few seconds at the most.) If you need to keep threads running for long periods of time, it is highly recommended you use the various APIs provided by&nbsp;</em>the package<em><code>java.util.concurrent</code></em><em>&nbsp;such&nbsp;</em>as,<em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/Executor.html\">Executor</a></code></em><em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/ThreadPoolExecutor.html\">ThreadPoolExecutor</a></code>&nbsp;</em>and.<em><code><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/java/util/concurrent/FutureTask.html\">FutureTask</a></code></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So you must move your queries to any services or any other thread maintainers. A simple example using Executor.class is given below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Executor myExecutor = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor();\nmyExecutor.execute<span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(() -&gt; {\n    myDao.insert(userObject);\n})</span>;</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Use&nbsp;<em>synchronized</em>&nbsp;for accessing database</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Usually, you only need one instance of the Room database for the whole app. In order to maintain this implementation, You have to create a singleton instance which gives the database instance using the synchronized method. So that, You can ensure the concurrent access of database is synchronized along the whole thread.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">//Sample database<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>class.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">\nstatic</span> UserDatabase INSTANCE;\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">\npublic</span><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> static</span> UserDatabase getDatabase(final Context context) {\n   <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(INSTANCE == null) {\n        synchronized (UserDatabase.class) {\n           <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(INSTANCE == null) {\n                INSTANCE = Room.databaseBuilder(context.getApplicationContext(),\n                        UserDatabase.class, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"database_name\"</span>)\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">                        .build</span>();\n\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n   <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> return </span>INSTANCE;\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bundle your queries together in DAO interface</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your query abstract function uses another&nbsp;two queries function, You can wrap them together in your DAO class. So that you can avoid boilerplate codes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Dao</span>\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">UserDao</span> </span>{\n    \n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Bundles to calls together here.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Transaction</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">open</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">updateData</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(users: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">User</span>&gt;)</span></span> {\n        deleteAllUsers()\n        insertAll(users)\n    }\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Insert</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">insertAll</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(users: <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">List</span>&lt;<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">User</span>&gt;)</span></span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Query(<span class=\"hljs-meta-string\">\"DELETE FROM Users\"</span>)</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">abstract</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fun</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">deleteAllUsers</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span></span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Reference:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room/\">https://developer.android.com/training/data-storage/room/</a>&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Room Database','','inherit','closed','closed','','92-revision-v1','','','2019-10-18 09:06:30','2019-10-18 08:06:30','',92,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/18/92-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(479,1,'2019-10-22 08:37:15','2019-10-22 07:37:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gradle is a build automation tool often used for JVM languages such as Java, Groovy or Scala. Gradle can be configured to run&nbsp;<code>Tasks</code>&nbsp;which do things like compile&nbsp;<code>jar</code>s, run tests, create documentation and much more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gardle is an advanced general purpose build management. It is an open source build automation system that builds up on ANT, Maven and lvy repositories. It supports groovy based Domain Specific Language (DSL) over the XML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"build-process\">The build process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process involves many tools and processes that convert your project into an Android Application Package (APK). The build process is very flexible, so it\'s useful to understand some of what is happening under the hood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":475,\"height\":534} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://developer.android.com/images/tools/studio/build-process_2x.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"534\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Figure 1.</strong>&nbsp;The build process of a typical Android app module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process for a typical Android app module, as shown in figure 1, follows these general steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The compilers convert your source code into DEX (Dalvik Executable) files, which include the bytecode that runs on Android devices, and everything else into compiled resources.</li><li>The APK Packager combines the DEX files and compiled resources into a single APK. Before your app can be installed and deployed onto an Android device, however, the APK must be signed.</li><li>The APK Packager signs your APK using either the debug or release keystore:<ol type=\"a\"><li>If you are building a debug version of your app, that is, an app you intend only for testing and profiling, the packager signs your app with the debug keystore. Android Studio automatically configures new projects with a debug keystore.</li><li>If you are building a release version of your app that you intend to release externally, the packager signs your app with the release keystore. To create a release keystore, read about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/publish/app-signing.html#studio\">signing your app in Android Studio</a>.</li></ol></li><li>Before generating your final APK, the packager uses the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/command-line/zipalign.html\">zipalign</a>&nbsp;tool to optimize your app to use less memory when running on a device.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the build process, you have either a debug APK or release APK of your app that you can use to deploy, test, or release to external users.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Gradle configuration</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>General structure.</strong>&nbsp;Follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/index.html\">Google\'s guide on Gradle for Android</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>minSdkVersion: 21</strong>&nbsp;We recommend to have a look at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/index.html#Platform\">Android version usage chart</a>&nbsp;before defining the minimum API required. Remember that the statistics given are global statistics and may differ when targeting a specific regional/demographic market. It is worth mentioning that some material design features are only available on Android 5.0 (API level 21) and above. And also, from API 21, the multidex support library is not needed anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <br><strong>Passwords.</strong>&nbsp;In your app\'s&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;you will need to define the&nbsp;<code>signingConfigs</code>&nbsp;for the release build. Here is what you should avoid: <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Don\'t do this</strong></em><strong>. </strong>This would appear in the version control system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\">signingConfigs </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\">release </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// DON\'T DO THIS!!</span>\n        storeFile file(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n        storePassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password123\"</span>\n        keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n        keyPassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password789\"</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead, make a&nbsp;<code>gradle.properties</code>&nbsp;file which should&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;be added to the version control system:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=password123\nKEY_PASSWORD=password789\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That file is automatically imported by Gradle, so you can use it in&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;as such:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">signingConfigs {\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            storeFile <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">file</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n            storePassword KEYSTORE_PASSWORD\n            keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n            keyPassword KEY_PASSWORD\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">ex</span>) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throw</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> InvalidUserDataException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"You should define KEYSTORE_PASSWORD and KEY_PASSWORD in gradle.properties.\"</span>)\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Use different package name for non-release builds</strong>&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use&nbsp;<code>applicationIdSuffix</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<em>debug</em><a href=\"http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/new-build-system/user-guide#TOC-Build-Types\">build type</a>&nbsp;to be able to install both&nbsp;<em>debug</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>release</em>&nbsp;apk on the same device (do this also for custom build types, if you need any). This will be especially valuable after your app has been published. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    buildTypes {\n        debug {\n            applicationIdSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'.debug\'</span>\n            versionNameSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'-DEBUG\'</span>\n        }\n\n        release {\n            // ...\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"building_gradle_minify\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#building_gradle_minify\">Removing unused resources and Java classes via resource shrinking</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Gradle build system for Android supports resource shrinking at build time. This automatically removes resources that are unused from the packaged application. In addition to that, this also removes unnecessary resources from libraries you are depending on. This can hugely reduce the size of your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To enable resource shrinking, update your build file similar to the following snippet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    ...\n\n    buildTypes {\n        release {\n            minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            shrinkResources <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-android.txt\'), <span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-rules.pro\'\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\">Defining dependencies and keeping the version external</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"bb4a\">1. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Module level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">25</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n    playServiceVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    \n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n   ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_12\">2. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Project level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>build.gradle(Project level)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">buildscript {\n    ...\n}\n\nallprojects {\n    ...\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'23.4.0\'</span>\n    playServicesVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'9.2.1\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> build.gradle(Module level) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span> \n\n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>  \n    ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Proguard</strong> <strong>configuration</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://proguard.sourceforge.net/\">ProGuard</a>&nbsp;is normally used on Android projects to shrink and obfuscate the packaged code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you are using ProGuard or not depends on your project configuration. Usually you would configure Gradle to use ProGuard when building a release APK.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">buildTypes</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">debug</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">minifyEnabled</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>\n    }\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">signingConfig</span> signingConfigs.release\n        minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n        proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-android.txt\'</span>), <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-rules.pro\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to determine which code has to be preserved and which code can be discarded or obfuscated, you have to specify one or more entry points to your code. These entry points are typically classes with main methods, applets, midlets, activities, etc. Android framework uses a default configuration which can be found from&nbsp;<code>SDK_HOME/tools/proguard/proguard-android.txt</code>. Using the above configuration, custom project-specific ProGuard rules, as defined in&nbsp;<code>my-project/app/proguard-rules.pro</code>, will be appended to the default configuration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A common problem related to ProGuard is to see the application crashing on startup with&nbsp;<code>ClassNotFoundException</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code>NoSuchFieldException</code>&nbsp;or similar, even though the build command (i.e.&nbsp;<code>assembleRelease</code>) succeeded without warnings. This means one out of two things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>ProGuard has removed the class, enum, method, field or annotation, considering it\'s not required.</li><li>ProGuard has obfuscated (renamed) the class, enum or field name, but it\'s being used indirectly by its original name, i.e. through Java reflection.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/usage.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been removed. Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been obfuscated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>stripping away</em>&nbsp;needed classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keep</code>&nbsp;options to your ProGuard config:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keep class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>obfuscating</em>&nbsp;classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keepnames</code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keepnames class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read more at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.guardsquare.com/en/proguard/manual/examples\">Proguard</a>&nbsp;for examples.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Early in your project, make and test release build</strong>&nbsp;to check whether ProGuard rules are correctly retaining your dependencies. Also whenever you include new libraries or update their dependencies, make a release build and test the APK on a device. Don\'t wait until your app is finally version \"1.0\" to make a release build, you might get several unpleasant surprises and a short time to fix them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip.</strong>&nbsp;Save the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for every release that you publish to your users. By retaining a copy of the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for each release build, you ensure that you can debug a problem if a user encounters a bug and submits an obfuscated stack trace.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>DexGuard</strong>. If you need hard-core tools for optimizing, and specially obfuscating release code, consider&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.saikoa.com/dexguard\">DexGuard</a>, a commercial software made by the same team that built ProGuard. It can also easily split Dex files to solve the 65k methods limitation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"leakcanary\">LeakCanary</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary is a memory leak detection library for Android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":649,\"height\":315} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img src=\"https://github.com/square/leakcanary/wiki/assets/screenshot-2.0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"649\" height=\"315\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary’s knowledge of the internals of the Android Framework gives it a unique ability to narrow down the cause of each leak, helping developers dramatically reduce OutOfMemoryError crashes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Add LeakCanary to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n  // <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation because LeakCanary should only run <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">in</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span> builds.\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation \'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android:<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2.0</span>-alpha-<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">3</span>\'\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>That’s it, there is no code change needed!</strong>&nbsp;LeakCanary will automatically show a notification when a memory leak is detected in debug builds.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/\">https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How do I exclude all instances of a transitive dependency when using Gradle?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can exclude a transitive dependency either by configuration or by dependency: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span>.all {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.webkit\"</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"webkit\"</span>\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fileTree</span>(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'*.jar\'</span>], dir: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'libs\'</span>) \n    implementation(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.1.0\"</span>) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.fragment\'</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'fragment\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to implement Remote binary dependency</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implementation</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android:app-magic:12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is actually shorthand for the following:<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">implementation <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">name</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'app-magic\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">version</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This declares a dependency on version 12.3 of the \"app-magic\" library, inside the \"com.example.android\" namespace group.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','inherit','closed','closed','','269-revision-v1','','','2019-10-22 08:37:15','2019-10-22 07:37:15','',269,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/22/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(481,1,'2019-10-22 08:42:57','2019-10-22 07:42:57','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gradle is a build automation tool often used for JVM languages such as Java, Groovy or Scala. Gradle can be configured to run&nbsp;<code>Tasks</code>&nbsp;which do things like compile&nbsp;<code>jar</code>s, run tests, create documentation and much more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gardle is an advanced general purpose build management. It is an open source build automation system that builds up on ANT, Maven and lvy repositories. It supports groovy based Domain Specific Language (DSL) over the XML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"build-process\">The build process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process involves many tools and processes that convert your project into an Android Application Package (APK). The build process is very flexible, so it\'s useful to understand some of what is happening under the hood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":475,\"height\":534} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://developer.android.com/images/tools/studio/build-process_2x.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"534\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Figure 1.</strong>&nbsp;The build process of a typical Android app module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process for a typical Android app module, as shown in figure 1, follows these general steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The compilers convert your source code into DEX (Dalvik Executable) files, which include the bytecode that runs on Android devices, and everything else into compiled resources.</li><li>The APK Packager combines the DEX files and compiled resources into a single APK. Before your app can be installed and deployed onto an Android device, however, the APK must be signed.</li><li>The APK Packager signs your APK using either the debug or release keystore:<ol type=\"a\"><li>If you are building a debug version of your app, that is, an app you intend only for testing and profiling, the packager signs your app with the debug keystore. Android Studio automatically configures new projects with a debug keystore.</li><li>If you are building a release version of your app that you intend to release externally, the packager signs your app with the release keystore. To create a release keystore, read about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/publish/app-signing.html#studio\">signing your app in Android Studio</a>.</li></ol></li><li>Before generating your final APK, the packager uses the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/command-line/zipalign.html\">zipalign</a>&nbsp;tool to optimize your app to use less memory when running on a device.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the build process, you have either a debug APK or release APK of your app that you can use to deploy, test, or release to external users.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Gradle configuration</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>General structure.</strong>&nbsp;Follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/index.html\">Google\'s guide on Gradle for Android</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>minSdkVersion: 21</strong>&nbsp;We recommend to have a look at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/index.html#Platform\">Android version usage chart</a>&nbsp;before defining the minimum API required. Remember that the statistics given are global statistics and may differ when targeting a specific regional/demographic market. It is worth mentioning that some material design features are only available on Android 5.0 (API level 21) and above. And also, from API 21, the multidex support library is not needed anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <br><strong>Passwords.</strong>&nbsp;In your app\'s&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;you will need to define the&nbsp;<code>signingConfigs</code>&nbsp;for the release build. Here is what you should avoid: <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Don\'t do this</strong></em><strong>. </strong>This would appear in the version control system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\">signingConfigs </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\">release </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// DON\'T DO THIS!!</span>\n        storeFile file(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n        storePassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password123\"</span>\n        keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n        keyPassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password789\"</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead, make a&nbsp;<code>gradle.properties</code>&nbsp;file which should&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;be added to the version control system:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=password123\nKEY_PASSWORD=password789\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That file is automatically imported by Gradle, so you can use it in&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;as such:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">signingConfigs {\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            storeFile <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">file</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n            storePassword KEYSTORE_PASSWORD\n            keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n            keyPassword KEY_PASSWORD\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">ex</span>) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throw</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> InvalidUserDataException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"You should define KEYSTORE_PASSWORD and KEY_PASSWORD in gradle.properties.\"</span>)\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Use different package name for non-release builds</strong>&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use&nbsp;<code>applicationIdSuffix</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<em>debug</em><a href=\"http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/new-build-system/user-guide#TOC-Build-Types\">build type</a>&nbsp;to be able to install both&nbsp;<em>debug</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>release</em>&nbsp;apk on the same device (do this also for custom build types, if you need any). This will be especially valuable after your app has been published. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    buildTypes {\n        debug {\n            applicationIdSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'.debug\'</span>\n            versionNameSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'-DEBUG\'</span>\n        }\n\n        release {\n            // ...\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"building_gradle_minify\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#building_gradle_minify\">Removing unused resources and Java classes via resource shrinking</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Gradle build system for Android supports resource shrinking at build time. This automatically removes resources that are unused from the packaged application. In addition to that, this also removes unnecessary resources from libraries you are depending on. This can hugely reduce the size of your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To enable resource shrinking, update your build file similar to the following snippet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    ...\n\n    buildTypes {\n        release {\n            minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            shrinkResources <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-android.txt\'), <span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-rules.pro\'\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\">Defining dependencies and keeping the version external</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"bb4a\">1. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Module level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">25</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n    playServiceVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    \n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n   ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_12\">2. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Project level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>build.gradle(Project level)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">buildscript {\n    ...\n}\n\nallprojects {\n    ...\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'23.4.0\'</span>\n    playServicesVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'9.2.1\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> build.gradle(Module level) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span> \n\n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>  \n    ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Proguard</strong> <strong>configuration</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://proguard.sourceforge.net/\">ProGuard</a>&nbsp;is normally used on Android projects to shrink and obfuscate the packaged code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you are using ProGuard or not depends on your project configuration. Usually you would configure Gradle to use ProGuard when building a release APK.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">buildTypes</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">debug</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">minifyEnabled</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>\n    }\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">signingConfig</span> signingConfigs.release\n        minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n        proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-android.txt\'</span>), <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-rules.pro\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to determine which code has to be preserved and which code can be discarded or obfuscated, you have to specify one or more entry points to your code. These entry points are typically classes with main methods, applets, midlets, activities, etc. Android framework uses a default configuration which can be found from&nbsp;<code>SDK_HOME/tools/proguard/proguard-android.txt</code>. Using the above configuration, custom project-specific ProGuard rules, as defined in&nbsp;<code>my-project/app/proguard-rules.pro</code>, will be appended to the default configuration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A common problem related to ProGuard is to see the application crashing on startup with&nbsp;<code>ClassNotFoundException</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code>NoSuchFieldException</code>&nbsp;or similar, even though the build command (i.e.&nbsp;<code>assembleRelease</code>) succeeded without warnings. This means one out of two things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>ProGuard has removed the class, enum, method, field or annotation, considering it\'s not required.</li><li>ProGuard has obfuscated (renamed) the class, enum or field name, but it\'s being used indirectly by its original name, i.e. through Java reflection.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/usage.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been removed. Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been obfuscated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>stripping away</em>&nbsp;needed classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keep</code>&nbsp;options to your ProGuard config:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keep class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>obfuscating</em>&nbsp;classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keepnames</code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keepnames class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read more at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.guardsquare.com/en/proguard/manual/examples\">Proguard</a>&nbsp;for examples.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Early in your project, make and test release build</strong>&nbsp;to check whether ProGuard rules are correctly retaining your dependencies. Also whenever you include new libraries or update their dependencies, make a release build and test the APK on a device. Don\'t wait until your app is finally version \"1.0\" to make a release build, you might get several unpleasant surprises and a short time to fix them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip.</strong>&nbsp;Save the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for every release that you publish to your users. By retaining a copy of the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for each release build, you ensure that you can debug a problem if a user encounters a bug and submits an obfuscated stack trace.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>DexGuard</strong>. If you need hard-core tools for optimizing, and specially obfuscating release code, consider&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.saikoa.com/dexguard\">DexGuard</a>, a commercial software made by the same team that built ProGuard. It can also easily split Dex files to solve the 65k methods limitation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"leakcanary\">LeakCanary</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary is a memory leak detection library for Android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":649,\"height\":315} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img src=\"https://github.com/square/leakcanary/wiki/assets/screenshot-2.0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"649\" height=\"315\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary’s knowledge of the internals of the Android Framework gives it a unique ability to narrow down the cause of each leak, helping developers dramatically reduce OutOfMemoryError crashes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Add LeakCanary to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n  // <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation because LeakCanary should only run <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">in</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span> builds.\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation \'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android:<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2.0</span>-alpha-<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">3</span>\'\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>That’s it, there is no code change needed!</strong>&nbsp;LeakCanary will automatically show a notification when a memory leak is detected in debug builds.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/\">https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How do I exclude all instances of a transitive dependency when using Gradle?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can exclude a transitive dependency either by configuration or by dependency: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span>.all {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.webkit\"</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"webkit\"</span>\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fileTree</span>(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'*.jar\'</span>], dir: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'libs\'</span>) \n    implementation(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.1.0\"</span>) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.fragment\'</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'fragment\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to implement Remote binary dependency</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implementation</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android:app-magic:12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is actually shorthand for the following:<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">implementation <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">name</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'app-magic\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">version</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This declares a dependency on version 12.3 of the \"app-magic\" library, inside the \"com.example.android\" namespace group.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','inherit','closed','closed','','269-revision-v1','','','2019-10-22 08:42:57','2019-10-22 07:42:57','',269,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/22/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(484,1,'2019-10-22 08:48:54','2019-10-22 07:48:54','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gradle is a build automation tool often used for JVM languages such as Java, Groovy or Scala. Gradle can be configured to run&nbsp;<code>Tasks</code>&nbsp;which do things like compile&nbsp;<code>jar</code>s, run tests, create documentation and much more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gardle is an advanced general purpose build management. It is an open source build automation system that builds up on ANT, Maven and lvy repositories. It supports groovy based Domain Specific Language (DSL) over the XML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"build-process\">The build process</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process involves many tools and processes that convert your project into an Android Application Package (APK). The build process is very flexible, so it\'s useful to understand some of what is happening under the hood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":475,\"height\":534} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://developer.android.com/images/tools/studio/build-process_2x.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"534\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Figure 1.</strong>&nbsp;The build process of a typical Android app module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The build process for a typical Android app module, as shown in figure 1, follows these general steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The compilers convert your source code into DEX (Dalvik Executable) files, which include the bytecode that runs on Android devices, and everything else into compiled resources.</li><li>The APK Packager combines the DEX files and compiled resources into a single APK. Before your app can be installed and deployed onto an Android device, however, the APK must be signed.</li><li>The APK Packager signs your APK using either the debug or release keystore:<ol type=\"a\"><li>If you are building a debug version of your app, that is, an app you intend only for testing and profiling, the packager signs your app with the debug keystore. Android Studio automatically configures new projects with a debug keystore.</li><li>If you are building a release version of your app that you intend to release externally, the packager signs your app with the release keystore. To create a release keystore, read about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/publish/app-signing.html#studio\">signing your app in Android Studio</a>.</li></ol></li><li>Before generating your final APK, the packager uses the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/command-line/zipalign.html\">zipalign</a>&nbsp;tool to optimize your app to use less memory when running on a device.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of the build process, you have either a debug APK or release APK of your app that you can use to deploy, test, or release to external users.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Gradle configuration</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>General structure.</strong>&nbsp;Follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/index.html\">Google\'s guide on Gradle for Android</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>minSdkVersion: 21</strong>&nbsp;We recommend to have a look at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://developer.android.com/about/dashboards/index.html#Platform\">Android version usage chart</a>&nbsp;before defining the minimum API required. Remember that the statistics given are global statistics and may differ when targeting a specific regional/demographic market. It is worth mentioning that some material design features are only available on Android 5.0 (API level 21) and above. And also, from API 21, the multidex support library is not needed anymore.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <br><strong>Passwords.</strong>&nbsp;In your app\'s&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;you will need to define the&nbsp;<code>signingConfigs</code>&nbsp;for the release build. Here is what you should avoid: <br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Don\'t do this</strong></em><strong>. </strong>This would appear in the version control system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-class\">signingConfigs </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-class\">release </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// DON\'T DO THIS!!</span>\n        storeFile file(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n        storePassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password123\"</span>\n        keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n        keyPassword <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"password789\"</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead, make a&nbsp;<code>gradle.properties</code>&nbsp;file which should&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;be added to the version control system:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=password123\nKEY_PASSWORD=password789\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That file is automatically imported by Gradle, so you can use it in&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>&nbsp;as such:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">signingConfigs {\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            storeFile <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">file</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"myapp.keystore\"</span>)\n            storePassword KEYSTORE_PASSWORD\n            keyAlias <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"thekey\"</span>\n            keyPassword KEY_PASSWORD\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">ex</span>) {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throw</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> InvalidUserDataException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"You should define KEYSTORE_PASSWORD and KEY_PASSWORD in gradle.properties.\"</span>)\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Use different package name for non-release builds</strong>&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use&nbsp;<code>applicationIdSuffix</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<em>debug</em><a href=\"http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/new-build-system/user-guide#TOC-Build-Types\">build type</a>&nbsp;to be able to install both&nbsp;<em>debug</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>release</em>&nbsp;apk on the same device (do this also for custom build types, if you need any). This will be especially valuable after your app has been published. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    buildTypes {\n        debug {\n            applicationIdSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'.debug\'</span>\n            versionNameSuffix <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'-DEBUG\'</span>\n        }\n\n        release {\n            // ...\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><strong>How to recompile with -Xlint:deprecation</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> adding this to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">allprojects {\n    ...\n\n    gradle<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.projectsEvaluated</span> {\n        tasks.withType(JavaCompile) {\n            options<span class=\"hljs-selector-class\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">.compilerArgs</span> &lt;&lt; <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"-Xlint:deprecation\"</span>\n        }\n    }   \n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"building_gradle_minify\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#building_gradle_minify\">Removing unused resources and Java classes via resource shrinking</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Gradle build system for Android supports resource shrinking at build time. This automatically removes resources that are unused from the packaged application. In addition to that, this also removes unnecessary resources from libraries you are depending on. This can hugely reduce the size of your application.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To enable resource shrinking, update your build file similar to the following snippet.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">android {\n    ...\n\n    buildTypes {\n        release {\n            minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            shrinkResources <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n            proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-android.txt\'), <span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard</span>-rules.pro\'\n        }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\"><a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/AndroidBuild/article.html#defining-dependencies-and-keeping-the-version-external\">Defining dependencies and keeping the version external</a></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"bb4a\">1. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Module level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">25</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n    playServiceVersion = \'<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>.<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>\'\n}\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    \n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$playServiceVersion\"</span>\n   ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_12\">2. Manage dependencies versions in same gradle file Project level</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>build.gradle(Project level)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">buildscript {\n    ...\n}\n\nallprojects {\n    ...\n}\n...\n\next {\n    supportLibraryVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'23.4.0\'</span>\n    playServicesVersion = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'9.2.1\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> build.gradle(Module level) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">apply plugin: \'com.android.application\'\nandroid {\n      ...\n    defaultConfig <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    buildTypes <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n    productFlavors <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">{...}</span>\n}\n...\n\ndependencies {\n    // <span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Android</span> supported libraries\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:appcompat-v7:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.android.support:design:$rootProject.supportLibraryVersion\"</span> \n\n    //<span class=\"hljs-type\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">Google</span> play services\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>\n    compile <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"com.google.android.gms:play-services-fitness:$rootProject.playServiceVersion\"</span>  \n    ...\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Proguard</strong> <strong>configuration</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"http://proguard.sourceforge.net/\">ProGuard</a>&nbsp;is normally used on Android projects to shrink and obfuscate the packaged code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you are using ProGuard or not depends on your project configuration. Usually you would configure Gradle to use ProGuard when building a release APK.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">buildTypes</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-section\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">debug</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">minifyEnabled</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>\n    }\n    release {\n        <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">signingConfig</span> signingConfigs.release\n        minifyEnabled <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>\n        proguardFiles getDefaultProguardFile(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-android.txt\'</span>), <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'proguard-rules.pro\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to determine which code has to be preserved and which code can be discarded or obfuscated, you have to specify one or more entry points to your code. These entry points are typically classes with main methods, applets, midlets, activities, etc. Android framework uses a default configuration which can be found from&nbsp;<code>SDK_HOME/tools/proguard/proguard-android.txt</code>. Using the above configuration, custom project-specific ProGuard rules, as defined in&nbsp;<code>my-project/app/proguard-rules.pro</code>, will be appended to the default configuration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A common problem related to ProGuard is to see the application crashing on startup with&nbsp;<code>ClassNotFoundException</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code>NoSuchFieldException</code>&nbsp;or similar, even though the build command (i.e.&nbsp;<code>assembleRelease</code>) succeeded without warnings. This means one out of two things:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>ProGuard has removed the class, enum, method, field or annotation, considering it\'s not required.</li><li>ProGuard has obfuscated (renamed) the class, enum or field name, but it\'s being used indirectly by its original name, i.e. through Java reflection.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/usage.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been removed. Check&nbsp;<code>app/build/outputs/proguard/release/mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;to see if the object in question has been obfuscated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>stripping away</em>&nbsp;needed classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keep</code>&nbsp;options to your ProGuard config:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keep class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To prevent ProGuard from&nbsp;<em>obfuscating</em>&nbsp;classes or class members, add a&nbsp;<code>keepnames</code>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>-keepnames class com.futurice.project.MyClass { *; }\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Read more at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.guardsquare.com/en/proguard/manual/examples\">Proguard</a>&nbsp;for examples.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Early in your project, make and test release build</strong>&nbsp;to check whether ProGuard rules are correctly retaining your dependencies. Also whenever you include new libraries or update their dependencies, make a release build and test the APK on a device. Don\'t wait until your app is finally version \"1.0\" to make a release build, you might get several unpleasant surprises and a short time to fix them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip.</strong>&nbsp;Save the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for every release that you publish to your users. By retaining a copy of the&nbsp;<code>mapping.txt</code>&nbsp;file for each release build, you ensure that you can debug a problem if a user encounters a bug and submits an obfuscated stack trace.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>DexGuard</strong>. If you need hard-core tools for optimizing, and specially obfuscating release code, consider&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.saikoa.com/dexguard\">DexGuard</a>, a commercial software made by the same team that built ProGuard. It can also easily split Dex files to solve the 65k methods limitation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"leakcanary\">LeakCanary</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary is a memory leak detection library for Android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"width\":649,\"height\":315} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img src=\"https://github.com/square/leakcanary/wiki/assets/screenshot-2.0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"649\" height=\"315\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>LeakCanary’s knowledge of the internals of the Android Framework gives it a unique ability to narrow down the cause of each leak, helping developers dramatically reduce OutOfMemoryError crashes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Add LeakCanary to&nbsp;<code>build.gradle</code>: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">dependencies {\n  // <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation because LeakCanary should only run <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">in</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span> builds.\n  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">debug</span>Implementation \'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android:<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2.0</span>-alpha-<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">3</span>\'\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>That’s it, there is no code change needed!</strong>&nbsp;LeakCanary will automatically show a notification when a memory leak is detected in debug builds.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/\">https://square.github.io/leakcanary/getting_started/</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>How do I exclude all instances of a transitive dependency when using Gradle?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can exclude a transitive dependency either by configuration or by dependency: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span>.all {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.webkit\"</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"webkit\"</span>\n}\n\n<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n    implementation <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">fileTree</span>(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span>: [<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'*.jar\'</span>], dir: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'libs\'</span>) \n    implementation(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.1.0\"</span>) {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'androidx.fragment\'</span>, module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'fragment\'</span>\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Or</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">configurations</span> {\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'axiom-compat\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'javax.servlet\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'commons-fileupload\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.apache.woden\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'javax.ws.rs\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// axiom-api</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'jaxen\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.apache.geronimo.specs\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> module: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'apache-mime4j-core\'</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// neethi</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">compile</span>.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">exclude</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.codehaus.woodstox\'</span>\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to implement Remote binary dependency</strong> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">implementation</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android:app-magic:12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is actually shorthand for the following:<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">implementation <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">group</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'com.example.android\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">name</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'app-magic\'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-attribute\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">version</span>: <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'12.3\'</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This declares a dependency on version 12.3 of the \"app-magic\" library, inside the \"com.example.android\" namespace group.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies\">https://developer.android.com/studio/build/dependencies</a> </li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Android Gradle','','inherit','closed','closed','','269-revision-v1','','','2019-10-22 08:48:54','2019-10-22 07:48:54','',269,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/10/22/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(487,1,'2019-11-04 05:19:23','2019-11-04 05:19:23','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Implementation Vs Api in Android&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies appearing in the&nbsp;<code>api</code>&nbsp;configurations will be transitively exposed to consumers of the library, and as such will appear on the compile classpath of consumers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies found in the&nbsp;<code>implementation</code>&nbsp;configuration will, on the other hand, not be exposed to consumers, and therefore not leak into the consumers\' compile classpath. This comes with several benefits:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa\">https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Calling startActivity() from outside of an Activity exception</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">    android.util.AndroidRuntimeException:</span> Calling startActivity() from outside of\n        an Activity  <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span> requires the FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK flag. Is this\n        really what you want?\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">android.app.ContextImpl.startActivity(ContextImpl.java:912)\n</span>\n    Solution :\n    Intent intent = new Intent(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>, YourActivity.class)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span>\n    intent.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK);\n</span>    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>.startActivity(intent)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"20a4\">Making a singleton class for Library</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>A singleton class is a class which can create only an object that can be shared all other classes.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">public class SingletonClass implements Serializable {\n    /* Step 4: Use volatile keyword to ensure that the Singleton is thread safe.  */\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> private</span><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> static</span> volatile SingletonClass sSoleInstance;\n\n    /*  Step 1: Make the<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> constructor</span> of the class as \'private\'. \n        This ensures that other classes are<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> not </span>able to create \n        a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the Singleton class.  */\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> private</span> SingletonClass(){\n\n        /*  Step 3: Ensure that the Singleton class is Reflection Proof. \n            A<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the Singleton can be created using Java Reflection API. \n            In order to prevent that, we need to<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> add </span>a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> check </span>to the<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> constructor</span>. \n            If the<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> constructor</span> is already initialized,<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> throw </span>a run-time exception.  */\n       <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(sSoleInstance != null){\n           <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> throw </span>new RuntimeException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Use getInstance() method to get the single instance of this class.\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    /*   \n     * Step 2: Create one<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> public</span><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> static</span> method to provide a single entry point to create a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the class. \n     * Check<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the class is available. If not, create a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the class.\n     */\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> public</span><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> static</span> SingletonClass getInstance() {\n       <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(sSoleInstance == null) {\n        \n            /* Step 4: Use Double Check locking method. This means make the Singleton class in the synchronized block \n            only<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>the<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>is null. So, the synchronized block will be executed only when the \'instance\' is null \n           <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> and </span>prevent unnecessary synchronization once the<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>variable is initialized.  */\n            synchronized (SingletonClass.class) {\n               <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> if </span>(sSoleInstance == null) sSoleInstance =<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>SingletonClass();\n            }\n        }\n\n       <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> return </span>sSoleInstance;\n    }\n\n\n    /* Step 5: Ensure that the Singleton class is safe from Serialization. When we need to implement \n     * Serializable interface in a Singleton class, we need to ensure that the<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>is maintained \n     * before<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> and </span>after serialization. By default when deserialized, a<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> new </span>instance of the Singleton class will be created. \n     * To prevent creation of another instance, implementat this method. \n     * This method replaces the object read from the stream<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> and </span>ensures that nobody can create another \n     *<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> instance </span>by serializing<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> and </span>deserializing the singleton.  */\n   <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\"> protected</span> SingletonClass readResolve() {\n       <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\"> return </span>getInstance();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Keep these things in mind for making library','','inherit','closed','closed','','421-revision-v1','','','2019-11-04 05:19:23','2019-11-04 05:19:23','',421,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/11/04/421-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(489,1,'2019-11-04 05:23:14','2019-11-04 05:23:14','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Implementation Vs Api in Android&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies appearing in the&nbsp;<code>api</code>&nbsp;configurations will be transitively exposed to consumers of the library, and as such will appear on the compile classpath of consumers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies found in the&nbsp;<code>implementation</code>&nbsp;configuration will, on the other hand, not be exposed to consumers, and therefore not leak into the consumers\' compile classpath. This comes with several benefits:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa\">https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Calling startActivity() from outside of an Activity exception</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">    android.util.AndroidRuntimeException:</span> Calling startActivity() from outside of\n        an Activity  <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span> requires the FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK flag. Is this\n        really what you want?\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">android.app.ContextImpl.startActivity(ContextImpl.java:912)\n</span>\n    Solution :\n    Intent intent = new Intent(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>, YourActivity.class)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span>\n    intent.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK);\n</span>    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>.startActivity(intent)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"20a4\">Making a singleton class for Library</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>A singleton class is a class which can create only an object that can be shared all other classes.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">SingletonClass</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">implements</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">Serializable</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/* Step 4: Use volatile keyword to ensure that the Singleton is thread safe.  */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> static <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">volatile</span> SingletonClass sSoleInstance;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*  Step 1: Make the constructor of the class as \'private\'. \n        This ensures that other classes are not able to create \n        a new instance of the Singleton class.  */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> SingletonClass(){\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*  Step 3: Ensure that the Singleton class is Reflection Proof. \n            A new instance of the Singleton can be created using Java Reflection API. \n            In order to prevent that, we need to add a check to the constructor. \n            If the constructor is already initialized, throw a run-time exception.  */</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (sSoleInstance != <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>){\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">throw</span> new RuntimeException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Use getInstance() method to get the single instance of this class.\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*   \n     * Step 2: Create one public static method to provide a single entry point to create a new instance of the class. \n     * Check if a new instance of the class is available. If not, create a new instance of the class.\n     */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> static SingletonClass getInstance() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (sSoleInstance == <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) {\n        \n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/* Step 4: Use Double Check locking method. This means make the Singleton class in the synchronized block \n            only if the instance is null. So, the synchronized block will be executed only when the \'instance\' is null \n            and prevent unnecessary synchronization once the instance variable is initialized.  */</span>\n            synchronized (SingletonClass.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span>) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (sSoleInstance == <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) sSoleInstance = new SingletonClass();\n            }\n        }\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> sSoleInstance;\n    }\n\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Step 5: Ensure that the Singleton class is safe from Serialization. When we need to implement </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Serializable interface in a Singleton class, we need to ensure that the instance is maintained </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// before and after serialization. By default when deserialized, a new instance of the Singleton class will be created. </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// To prevent creation of another instance, implementat this method. </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// This method replaces the object read from the stream and ensures that nobody can create another </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// instance by serializing and deserializing the singleton.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">protected</span> SingletonClass readResolve() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> getInstance();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Keep these things in mind for making library','','inherit','closed','closed','','421-revision-v1','','','2019-11-04 05:23:14','2019-11-04 05:23:14','',421,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/11/04/421-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(491,1,'2019-11-04 06:20:04','2019-11-04 06:20:04','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Implementation Vs Api in Android&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies appearing in the&nbsp;<code>api</code>&nbsp;configurations will be transitively exposed to consumers of the library, and as such will appear on the compile classpath of consumers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependencies found in the&nbsp;<code>implementation</code>&nbsp;configuration will, on the other hand, not be exposed to consumers, and therefore not leak into the consumers\' compile classpath. This comes with several benefits:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa\">https://medium.com/mindorks/implementation-vs-api-in-gradle-3-0-494c817a6fa</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Calling startActivity() from outside of an Activity exception</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-symbol\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">    android.util.AndroidRuntimeException:</span> Calling startActivity() from outside of\n        an Activity  <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span> requires the FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK flag. Is this\n        really what you want?\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">android.app.ContextImpl.startActivity(ContextImpl.java:912)\n</span>\n    Solution :\n    Intent intent = new Intent(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>, YourActivity.class)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span>\n    intent.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK);\n</span>    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">context</span>.startActivity(intent)<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">;</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"20a4\">Making a singleton class for Library</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>A singleton class is a class which can create only an object that can be shared all other classes.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; padding: 0.5em; background: rgb(240, 240, 240); color: rgb(68, 68, 68);\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">SingletonClass</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">implements</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">Serializable</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">/* Step 4: Use volatile keyword to ensure that the Singleton is thread safe. \n     * The value of a volatile variable will never be stored in the cache. All read and write will be done from and to the main memory.*/</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">volatile</span> SingletonClass sSoleInstance;\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">/*  Step 1: Make the constructor of the class as \'private\'. \n        This ensures that other classes are not able to create \n        a new instance of the Singleton class.  */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">SingletonClass</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">()</span></span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">/*  Step 3: Ensure that the Singleton class is Reflection Proof. \n            A new instance of the Singleton can be created using Java Reflection API. \n            In order to prevent that, we need to add a check to the constructor. \n            If the constructor is already initialized, throw a run-time exception.  */</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">if</span> (sSoleInstance != <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">null</span>){\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">throw</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">new</span> RuntimeException(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0);\">\"Use getInstance() method to get the single instance of this class.\"</span>);\n        }\n    }\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">/*   \n     * Step 2: Create one public static method to provide a single entry point to create a new instance of the class. \n     * Check if a new instance of the class is available. If not, create a new instance of the class.\n     */</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">static</span> SingletonClass <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">getInstance</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">()</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">if</span> (sSoleInstance == <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">null</span>) {\n        \n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">/* Step 4: Use Double Check locking method. This means make the Singleton class in the synchronized block \n            only if the instance is null. So, the synchronized block will be executed only when the \'instance\' is null \n            and prevent unnecessary synchronization once the instance variable is initialized.  */</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">synchronized</span> (SingletonClass.class) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">if</span> (sSoleInstance == <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">null</span>) sSoleInstance = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">new</span> SingletonClass();\n            }\n        }\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">return</span> sSoleInstance;\n    }\n\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// Step 5: Ensure that the Singleton class is safe from Serialization. When we need to implement </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// Serializable interface in a Singleton class, we need to ensure that the instance is maintained </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// before and after serialization. By default when deserialized, a new instance of the Singleton class will be created. </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// To prevent creation of another instance, implementat this method. </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// This method replaces the object read from the stream and ensures that nobody can create another </span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 136, 136);\">// instance by serializing and deserializing the singleton.</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">protected</span> SingletonClass <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(136, 0, 0); font-weight: 700;\">readResolve</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">()</span> </span>{\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"font-weight: 700;\">return</span> getInstance();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Keep these things in mind for making library','','inherit','closed','closed','','421-revision-v1','','','2019-11-04 06:20:04','2019-11-04 06:20:04','',421,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/11/04/421-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(494,1,'2019-11-09 07:04:22','2019-11-09 07:04:22','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely popular and are often used in almost any Android project. Each has different purposes but all of them make life as a developer much more pleasant. The major libraries are listed below in a few categories.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_10\">OCRSdk</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Text Detector from image for react native using Google Vision API on android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ocrsdk:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage Method</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">     scanner = OCRSdk.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).addListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> OCRListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onSuccess(StringBuilder result) {\n                tvStatus.setText(result);\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedLines(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; lines) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedWords(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; words) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onFailure(Exception e) {\n\n            }\n        });\n        scanner.addTextView(tvStatus, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> SentenceDetector.OnClickListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onClick(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> word) {\n\n            }\n        });\n\n        scanner.startScanning();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"markdown-header-progressbutton\">ProgressButton</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nShow button with progress bar\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Android Button that morphs into a loading progress bar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Fully customizable in the XML</li><li>Really simple to use.</li><li>Makes your app looks cooler</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/73ab06601fb650fd51fa01781053fde8ff52f9bd/68747470733a2f2f692e737461636b2e696d6775722e636f6d2f38534852312e676966\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Setup\nAdd this <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">to</span> your project build.gradle\n\nallprojects {\n    repositories {\n        maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Dependency\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//before androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButton:1.0\'</span>\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//after androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButtonX:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Usage\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// In your activity_main.xml class:</span>\n\n &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span> layout=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@layout/button_progress\"</span>/&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for activity</span>\nView rootView = activity.getWindow().getDecorView().getRootView();\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for fragment pass layout reference in view</span>\nrootView = view;\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//  Initialization method</span>\nbtnAction = ProgressButton.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, rootView)\n        .setText(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Send Request\"</span>)\n        .setOnClickListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> View.OnClickListener() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onClick</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(View v)</span> </span>{\n            }\n        });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Update progress bar methods</span>\n     \n      btnAction.startProgress();\n\n    \n      btnAction.revertSuccessProgress(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ProgressButton.Listener() {\n          @Override\n          public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onAnimationCompleted() {\n          }\n      });\n      \n      btnAction.revertProgress();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CoreLib</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This library contains Android Button which can morph to Circular Progress,    Progress manager used for showing progress bar during making http request with success and failure response handler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link:  <br><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib\" target=\"_blank\">https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>DBInterface</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> SQLite databases is tough while developing. You cannot view the tables, you don\'t know what is getting inserted into the tables and you can\'t update the data and see how your application responds to it. What if you had a database manager like oracle sql developr, mysql work bench for your application\'s SQLite database? This library gives you that. With this library you can manage the database of your android app from the app itself. You can view, insert, delete, update the tables of your app\'s SQLite database from your app. <strong><br>Also Support Android Room Library</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Github link:  <a href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_1\">FirebaseConfig</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setup firebase Remote Config and Crashlist for validating user and crash reporting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link :<br><a href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\">ht</a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\">tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig</a><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"markdown-header-exporter\">Exporter</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Export support in following format: (txt, csv, xls) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>1. Text file</li><li>2. CSV file</li><li>Excel file</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-dependency\">Dependency</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<embed type=\"image/svg+xml\" src=\"https://jitpack.io/v/org.bitbucket.droidhelios/Exporter.svg\" />\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:Exporter:x.y\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-prepare-list-for-this-library\">Prepare List for this library</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; getExporterList() {\n        List&lt;User&gt; yourList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"01\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Alpha\"</span>));\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"02\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Bita\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//add header in your exporting list</span>\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Id\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Name\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//make exporter list</span>\n        List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; exporterList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> (User item : yourList){\n            exporterList.add(Arrays.asList(item.getId(),item.getName()));\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> exporterList;\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-text-file\">Export in Text file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).TextBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleText\"</span>)\n            .setFileBody(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello World!\"</span>)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-csv-file\">Export in CSV file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).CsvBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleCsv\"</span>)\n            .setCsvData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-excel-file\">Export in Excel file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).ExcelBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleExcel\"</span>)\n            .setExcelData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Success\"</span>, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>\n\nFor showing list of files.\n\n</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> exportCsv.showListOfFiles(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Selector&lt;File&gt;() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSelect</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n            shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n        }\n    });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Must Have Libraries For Android Developer','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2019-11-09 07:04:22','2019-11-09 07:04:22','',274,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/11/09/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(496,1,'2019-11-09 07:06:50','2019-11-09 07:06:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many third-party libraries for Android but several of them are \"must have\" libraries that are extremely popular and are often used in almost any Android project. Each has different purposes but all of them make life as a developer much more pleasant. The major libraries are listed below in a few categories.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_10\">OCRSdk</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Text Detector from image for react native using Google Vision API on android.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ocrsdk:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Usage Method</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">     scanner = OCRSdk.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).addListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> OCRListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onSuccess(StringBuilder result) {\n                tvStatus.setText(result);\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedLines(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; lines) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onDetectedWords(List&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; words) {\n\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onFailure(Exception e) {\n\n            }\n        });\n        scanner.addTextView(tvStatus, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> SentenceDetector.OnClickListener() {\n            @Override\n            public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onClick(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> word) {\n\n            }\n        });\n\n        scanner.startScanning();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"markdown-header-progressbutton\">ProgressButton</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nShow button with progress bar\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Android Button that morphs into a loading progress bar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Fully customizable in the XML</li><li>Really simple to use.</li><li>Makes your app looks cooler</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/73ab06601fb650fd51fa01781053fde8ff52f9bd/68747470733a2f2f692e737461636b2e696d6775722e636f6d2f38534852312e676966\" alt=\"enter image description here\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Setup\nAdd this <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">to</span> your project build.gradle\n\nallprojects {\n    repositories {\n        maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n    }\n}</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Dependency\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">dependencies</span> {\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//before androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButton:1.0\'</span>\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//after androidX</span>\n        implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:ProgressButtonX:1.0\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Usage\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// In your activity_main.xml class:</span>\n\n &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">include</span> layout=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@layout/button_progress\"</span>/&gt;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for activity</span>\nView rootView = activity.getWindow().getDecorView().getRootView();\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// for fragment pass layout reference in view</span>\nrootView = view;\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//  Initialization method</span>\nbtnAction = ProgressButton.newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, rootView)\n        .setText(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Send Request\"</span>)\n        .setOnClickListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> View.OnClickListener() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onClick</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(View v)</span> </span>{\n            }\n        });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//Update progress bar methods</span>\n     \n      btnAction.startProgress();\n\n    \n      btnAction.revertSuccessProgress(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ProgressButton.Listener() {\n          @Override\n          public <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> onAnimationCompleted() {\n          }\n      });\n      \n      btnAction.revertProgress();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CoreLib</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This library contains Android Button which can morph to Circular Progress,    Progress manager used for showing progress bar during making http request with success and failure response handler.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link:  <br><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib\" target=\"_blank\">https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/amitresearchdev/corelib</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>DBInterface</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> SQLite databases is tough while developing. You cannot view the tables, you don\'t know what is getting inserted into the tables and you can\'t update the data and see how your application responds to it. What if you had a database manager like oracle sql developr, mysql work bench for your application\'s SQLite database? This library gives you that. With this library you can manage the database of your android app from the app itself. You can view, insert, delete, update the tables of your app\'s SQLite database from your app. <strong><br>Also Support Android Room Library</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Github link:  <a href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://github.com/Droidhelios/DBInterface\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"mce_1\">FirebaseConfig</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Setup firebase Remote Config and Crashlist for validating user and crash reporting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bitbucket link :<br><a href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\">ht</a><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\">tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig</a><br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"tps://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://amitresearchdev@bitbucket.org/droidres/firebaseconfig.git\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"markdown-header-exporter\">Exporter</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Export support in following format: (txt, csv, xls) </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Text file</li><li>CSV file</li><li>Excel file</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-dependency\">Dependency</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<embed type=\"image/svg+xml\" src=\"https://jitpack.io/v/org.bitbucket.droidhelios/Exporter.svg\">\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    allprojects {\n        repositories {\n            maven { url <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'https://jitpack.io\'</span> }\n        }\n    }\n    dependencies { \n       implementation <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'org.bitbucket.droidhelios:Exporter:x.y\'</span>\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-prepare-list-for-this-library\">Prepare List for this library</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; getExporterList() {\n        List&lt;User&gt; yourList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"01\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Alpha\"</span>));\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"02\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Bita\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//add header in your exporting list</span>\n        yourList.add(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>, <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> User(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Id\"</span>,<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Name\"</span>));\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//make exporter list</span>\n        List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; exporterList = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> (User item : yourList){\n            exporterList.add(Arrays.asList(item.getId(),item.getName()));\n        }\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> exporterList;\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-text-file\">Export in Text file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).TextBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleText\"</span>)\n            .setFileBody(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello World!\"</span>)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-csv-file\">Export in CSV file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).CsvBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleCsv\"</span>)\n            .setCsvData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"markdown-header-export-in-excel-file\">Export in Excel file</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">Exporter.getInstance(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>).ExcelBuilder()\n            .setFileName(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"SampleExcel\"</span>)\n            .setExcelData(exporterList)\n            .setListener(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Callback&lt;File&gt;() {\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSuccess</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Success\"</span>, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onFailure</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(Exception e)</span> </span>{\n                    Toast.makeText(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, e.getMessage(), Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();\n\n                }\n            }).export();</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>\n\nFor showing list of files.\n\n</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"> exportCsv.showListOfFiles(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Selector&lt;File&gt;() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">onSelect</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(File result)</span> </span>{\n            shareFile(MainActivity.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>, result);\n        }\n    });</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Must Have Libraries For Android Developer','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2019-11-09 07:06:50','2019-11-09 07:06:50','',274,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/11/09/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(499,1,'2019-12-21 07:43:28','2019-12-21 07:43:28','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Browse sample code to learn how to build different components for your applications.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This section covers useful codes for Java Android Programming. Every example program includes the description of the program, Java Android code, explanation as well as output of the program. <br>Below are Android Code Examples, Tutorials and projects to make android applications:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-class\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">class</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">HomeListData</span></span>{\n\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span>&lt;ClassModel&gt; getClassModels(){\n        ...\n        ...\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;() ;\n        }\n    }\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> void initClassModel(){\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n            Method method = HomeListData.class.getMethod(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"getClassModels\"</span>);\n            Object o = method.invoke(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span> );\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( o <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span> Collection<span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">&lt;?</span>&gt;){\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span> = (<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">List</span>) o ;\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span>.size() &gt; <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span> &amp;&amp; <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span>.get(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span>  ClassModel ) {\n                    classModels = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">for</span> ( Object classModel :  <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">list</span> ) {\n                        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( classModel <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">instanceof</span> ClassModel ) {\n                            classModels.add((ClassModel)classModel);\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (NoSuchMethodException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (IllegalAccessException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (InvocationTargetException e) {\n            e.printStackTrace();\n        }<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">finally</span> {\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> ( classModels == <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">null</span> || classModels.size() &lt; <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span> ){\n                finish();\n            }\n        }\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Android TextView : “Do not concatenate text displayed with setText”</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> helloWorld = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Hello\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"World\"</span>);\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> count = getString(R.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">string</span>.hello_world_count, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">10</span>);\n\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> totalCount = <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Total : $count\"</span>;</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> world <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">at</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">position</span> <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\'$s\'</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;Hello - %s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> hello world\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world\"</span>&gt;%<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s - %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$s&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">set</span> <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">numeric</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">value</span>\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"hello_world_count\"</span>&gt;%d Item Selected&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    // example\n    &lt;<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">name</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"welcome_messages\"</span>&gt;Hello, %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">1</span>$s! You have %<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">2</span>$d <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> messages.&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">string</span>&gt;\n    //<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">using</span> getString(R.string.welcome_message, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"Test\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">0</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don\'t get confused with&nbsp;<strong>%1$s</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>%2$d</strong>&nbsp;in the accepted answer.Here is a few extra information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>The format specifiers can be of the following syntax:</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>%[<code>argument_index</code>$]<code>format_specifier</code></p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>The optional&nbsp;<strong>argument_index</strong>&nbsp;is specified as a number ending with a “$” after the “%” and selects the specified argument in the argument list. The first argument is referenced by&nbsp;<strong>\"1$\"</strong>, the second by&nbsp;<strong>\"2$\"</strong>, etc.</li><li>The required&nbsp;<strong>format specifier</strong>&nbsp;is a character indicating how the argument should be formatted. The set of valid conversions for a given argument depends on the argument\'s&nbsp;<strong>data type.</strong></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 id=\"mce_3\">How can I show the shadow only on the bottom side of the layout </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nAn important thing here is the attribute&nbsp;<code>outlineProvider</code>, that is required to make the outer Layout cast a shadow even without having a background set.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"xml\"><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span> \n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_width</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"match_parent\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:layout_height</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"wrap_content\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:background</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"@android:color/white\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:elevation</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"2dp\"</span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-attr\">android:outlineProvider</span>=<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"bounds\"</span> &gt;</span>\n <span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">&lt;/<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">LinearLayout</span>&gt;</span>\n</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Validate URL</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">    <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">static</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">boolean</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">isValidURL</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">(String urlStr)</span> </span>{\n          <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>  Patterns.WEB_URL.matcher(urlStr).matches();\n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>UI post delay by time interval using Handler</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler().postDelayed(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{ \n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// write your code here</span>\n            }\n        }, <span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">400</span>);</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Useful for small background tasks</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//        Declear in class </span>\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">final</span> Handler <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span> = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Handler();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Thread(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n            <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Try to sleep the thread for 20 milliseconds</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">try</span> {\n                    Thread.sleep(<span class=\"hljs-number\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">20</span>);  <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//3 seconds</span>\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">catch</span> (InterruptedException e) {\n                    e.printStackTrace();\n                }\n\n                <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Update the progress bar</span>\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">handler</span>.post(<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">new</span> Runnable() {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-meta\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">@Override</span>\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 126, 231);\">run</span><span class=\"hljs-params\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">()</span> </span>{\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">//                             updateUi()</span>\n                    }\n                });\n            }\n        }).start(); <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">// Start the operation</span></pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>How do I escape a single quote in SQL Query</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">word</span>.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">replace</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"\'\'\"</span>)</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Http request using webView  </h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">private</span> void callWebviewAuth() {\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web = (WebView)findViewById();\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.getSettings().setJavaScriptEnabled(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearCache(<span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">true</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.clearHistory(); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.loadUrl(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"https://www.facebook.com/v2.6/dialog/oauth?redirect_uri=fb464891386855067%3A%2F%2Fauthorize%2F&amp;scope=user_birthday,user_photos,user_education_history,email,user_relationship_details,user_friends,user_work_history,user_likes&amp;response_type=token%2Csigned_request&amp;client_id=464891386855067\"</span>);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.web.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient(){\n            String authCode;\n            boolean authComplete = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">false</span>;\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onFormResubmission(WebView webView, Message message, Message message2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onFormResubmission(webView, message, message2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onLoadResource(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onLoadResource(webView, string2);\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-comment\" style=\"color: rgb(118, 110, 107);\">/*\n             * Enabled aggressive block sorting\n             */</span>\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageFinished(WebView webView, String string2) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageFinished(webView, string2); \n                Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1 = string2;\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (Login.<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.url1.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"access_token=\"</span>) &amp;&amp; !<span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">this</span>.authComplete) {\n                     \n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                } <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">else</span> {\n                    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span> (!string2.contains((CharSequence)<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"error=access_denied\"</span>)) <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    {\n                        \n                        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span>;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> void onPageStarted(WebView webView, String string2, Bitmap bitmap) {\n                <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">super</span>.onPageStarted(webView, string2, bitmap);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4388992/key-hash-for-android-facebook-app\">Key hash for Android-&nbsp;Facebook&nbsp;Login</a></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are the steps-</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Download openssl from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8k_WIN32.zip\"><strong>Google code</strong></a>&nbsp;(If you have a 64 bit machine you must&nbsp;<a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/openssl-for-windows/downloads/detail?name=openssl-0.9.8e_X64.zip&amp;can=2&amp;q=\"><strong>download openssl-0.9.8e X64</strong></a>&nbsp;not the latest version)</li><li>Extract it. create a folder- OpenSSL in C:/ and copy the extracted code here.</li><li>detect debug.keystore file path. If u didn\'t find, then do a search in C:/ and use the Path in the command in next step.</li><li>open cmd and change directory cd \"C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_191\\bin\" </li><li>run keytool command mentioned below.<ul><li>it will ask for password, put android</li><li>that\'s all. u will get a key-hash </li></ul></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\">keytool -exportcert -alias androiddebugkey -keystore \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">Users</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">kkk</span></span>.android<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">debug</span></span>.keystore\" | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" sha1 -binary | \"C:<span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">OpenSSL</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">bin</span></span><span class=\"hljs-tag\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">\\<span class=\"hljs-name\" style=\"color: rgb(242, 44, 64);\">openssl</span></span>\" base64</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>Pass data in fragment using Arguments</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nThe underlying Binder transaction buffer has a limited fixed size, currently 1Mb, which is shared by all transactions in progress for the process.\n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<pre class=\"hljs\" style=\"display: block; overflow-x: auto; background: rgb(241, 239, 238); color: rgb(104, 97, 94); padding: 0.5em;\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> static Fragment newInstance(<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data1, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span> data2, ArrayList&lt;<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">String</span>&gt; <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>) {\n        Fragment fragment = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Fragment(); \n        Bundle bundle = <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">new</span> Bundle();\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data1\"</span>, data1);\n        bundle.putString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data2\"</span>, data2);\n        bundle.putParcelableArrayList(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"list\"</span>, <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span>);\n        fragment.setArguments(bundle); \n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">return</span> fragment;\n    }\n    \n    @Override\n    <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">public</span> <span class=\"hljs-literal\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">void</span> onCreate(@Nullable Bundle savedInstanceState) {\n        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n        <span class=\"hljs-keyword\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 234);\">if</span>(getArguments()!=<span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">null</span>) {\n            data1 = getArguments().getString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data1\"</span>);\n            data2 = getArguments().getString(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"data2\"</span>);\n            <span class=\"hljs-built_in\" style=\"color: rgb(223, 83, 32);\">list</span> = getArguments().getParcelableArrayList(<span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: rgb(123, 151, 38);\">\"list\"</span>);\n        } \n    }</pre>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Useful Codes','','inherit','closed','closed','','278-revision-v1','','','2019-12-21 07:43:28','2019-12-21 07:43:28','',278,'http://blogs.appsfeature.com/index.php/2019/12/21/278-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
